{"text": "Gun Wings is a surprisingly good bullet-hell game for veterans of shmups. It uses the same shield mechanic from Ikarua; if your ship is the same color as the bullets, you don't die. The only difference is that you pick your ship color in the beginning and you're stuck with it the entire run. There are three ships/girls you can choose from, Hakuchou(yellow), Kou(red), and Uguisu(blue). Hakuchou has the most spread, Uguisu has the best forward attack, and Kou can attack behind her and has a massive damage ability. The only cons I can say are the game is short and the gameplay is a bit generic but I can't complain too much since the game is only $2 at the time of this review. The game's levels and difficulty will change depending on the ship you choose, such as the color of the bullets changing to make the game harder. Easy and normal difficulty are too easy for veterans so I would recommend hard or nightmare (unlocks after finishing the game on hard). Uguisu was the hardest for me because she lacks the spread and her charge up ability does damage over time rather than a big damage up front, but she is still the waifu because she wears schoolgirl uniform in the first 3 stages :^) Overall, it was a fun experience and it is very worth if you can get it on sale.", "appid": "348240", "steamid": "profiles/76561198043266394", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1605009600.0}
