{"text": "DATE : 15-Jan-2019  SETUP :  Windows 10 64-Bit, MS Surface Book 2016 (GTX 965M) Laptop, Logitech G700s Mouse RATING : A for Optimization C for Storytelling A for Visual Immersion  A for Aural Immersion A for Control A for Fun Factor A for Value REVIEW : The game ran smooth without problem at 1080p 60fps with very high graphic settings (no AA). It have mediocre storytelling and characters, but the visual and aural presentation are really good with smart level designs. The puzzles feel indigenous and provide satisfaction once you solve them. The combat parts also fun, the enemy AI smart enough to flank you or flush you out of hiding with grenades. With hard difficulty setting, I spent 15H to get all the treasure collectibles and finish the story. The puzzles took time to solve since the \"notepad\" that provide hints to your character is pretty useless in hard setting. NOTES : 1. Some of the multiplayer-related steam achievements are broken, so you can't 100% this game.  2. Low player base for multiplayer.", "appid": "231330", "steamid": "profiles/76561198084239937", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "9", "votes_funny": "3", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1547467200.0}
