{"text": "The Beautiful -The story drives you to keep on playing and see the end of the game.  -The art style is diverse and you can tell they took pride in the anime cutscenes.  -There’s no characters that feel like they are there just for filler, each character has a story and they aren't bland either, they all look hella unique.  -The amount of effort and time they must've spent making this game with the amount of detail in dialogue and characters is insane.  The Good -Theres alot of things to have happen around the world from minigames to fighting arenas.  -There's a few side missions so it doesn't drive you crazily from the main story. -The combat is easy to get use to and feels decent. -The inventory system and fashion system is easy to learn and knowing what's good is fairly easy.  -The enemies you fight will look interesting and there's a ton of different ones.  -Very little to none fan service in this game and to me fan service will ruin and good story. The game runs really good on a normal set up.  The Bad -The story can be difficult to follow at times if you take long breaks between playing.  -There's some moments of downtime like every time you have to climb something, if it's tall enough it will be noticeable. -Most  of the time when you go to a new location you most likely will never go back there again because there is no reason to. -There are some bugs in the menu that had me stuck for a short hour but after i figured it out, it never broke again.  The Ugly -The puzzles are horrendous, you have to turn this lever to open this door, oh wait, to get to this lever you have to press this lever it just seems repetitive. -You will have moments where you just running avoiding enemies just to get to the objective and that can take some time.  Final Thoughts -Use a controller since this is a console port.  -Once i picked it up for an hour, i sat there for a good 5 hrs and never wanted to put the game down. -Worth the price.  Short Summary Personally, i don't like to know much about a game beside if the story is good, so i decided to make a short summary for those people. This is my first JRPG and im honestly so thankful i played it so if it's your first it will a great entry to the genre. The story is amazing, each character is so interesting i wanted to know more and more about these characters as time went on. The environment is filled with things to do such as minigames. The combat is very button mashy and you don't have to put that much effort on the combos but you should focus on the strategy part of the combat. The artstyle is cool because it goes from 3d to anime cutscenes and the art of the world is interesting. The gameplay can feel repetitive and confusing sometimes because there's rare puzzles that you have to do to pass certain areas. The enemies surround the open world like the enemies in wizard101 funny enough. If you dodge them they won't fight you but if your not paying attention, you will get caught off guard.  \"Why Do Birds Fly?\"", "appid": "429660", "steamid": "profiles/76561198067278149", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1548849600.0}
