{"text": "(-) Performance issues:  The matchmaking is a bummer compared to BL2 (it's like playing with 200+ ping in Counter Strike). Bosses: I'm sad to say the boss fights are total horse ♥♥♥♥♥, worst in the franchise and the only boss worth the hype is Maliwan (simply adding shield to bosses doesn't make them fun, Maliwan fight was done correctly) (+) Feeling: The game feels fresh, probably because I'm used to BL2 but it felt like the gun mechanics are better alongside the movement and feel. Customizing: Almost endless amount of character skill combinations alongside the weapons perks and other gear.  Story: The story is fantastic and sticks to what the franchise is known for. Several plot twists that I didn't expect and I expect for some things to be given clarity in DLCs. DLCs: I really enjoy the casino and the tentacle ones, can't wait for more! :D Recommend BL2 if you are on a budget and/or new to the franchise. Recommend BL3 if you want the newest experiences.", "appid": "397540", "steamid": "profiles/76561198113962160", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "6", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1584705600.0}
