{"text": "Ryse: Son of Rome is third-person action game developed by Crytek.Most of us knows this developer for Crysis.Son of Rome was an Xbox One exclusive title but was later ported to the PC and had improved graphic. This game tells us history about  Roman Warrior, Marius Titus, son of legendary Roman general.At the beginning of game his family was cruelly killed by fake barbarians.He quickly rises through the Legion ranks searching for the people behind his family's murder while, at the same time, fighting for Rome.Generally all battles with our participation will take place in wild lands of Britannia (with various warring barbarian factions). 1.Brutal punishments (It really looks very effective,much blood and the torn-off extremities.I like it very much. 2.MAGNIFICENT graphic and visual effects.  my opinion it was very interesting story,with nice cut-scenes and effective ending. 4.It is surprisingly good port from console.It happens in very rare cases. 5.Atmosphere.Fans of Ancient Rome will be happy. 1.Very short story.It's the biggest minus.I've completed it within 7-8 hours in normal mode. 2.Lack of different terrains.For example something like desert or a snowy. 3.Little variation of attack moves. 4.Not completely finished RPG elements.I think it worth improving. In conclusion I wanna say that it's a good game but not everyone can estimate it. Ryse: Son of Rome is for people who likes the atmosphere of Ancient Rome, extreme and entertaining violence.Especially if you have a Medium or High End gaming system cause it promises magnificent cinematic effects(so you can use a game as a Benchmark for your PC).It is necessary to buy in case of sale.If Crytek will announce a sequel of RYSE i'll buy it.", "appid": "302510", "steamid": "profiles/76561198116196137", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1431259200.0}
