{"text": "Planet Explorers I've spent over 1K hours exploring, crafting and building in a game world that can be played in Story mode to learn all the basic controls. Adventure mode for a vast array of world types for single player. Also has a build mode where you have infinite resources to use to design or tweak items in the creation Editor. It also use to have Multiplayer and Co-op playing modes. Due to a server crash which had controlled all multiplayer and Co-op, that lost all that data for those modes ... the game is now free to play.   Story mode is probably advised to be used to learn all the controls, where for doing simple fetch quests you can be rewarded with scripts. For items you'll be able to craft or use. Most items or scripts could also be bought for money, if you find an npc that has a selling topic. Well actually the money at the start of the game is Meat so all enemies you kill increases your money. The story will lead you though the races and history of the Planet Maria that you have crash landed on.  The story is okay though most that happens is well broadcast beforehand.  Where your main role is building a colony to gather and train npcs in skills to help in defending the colony from attacks. Building a well defended colony with lots of defending turrets as well as reliable npcs. Planet Explorers makes digging tunnels or excavating underground bunkers easy, even diverting flowing water to your colony.   To help with this the game has a creation engine in which you can create almost anything from weapons, vehicles, buildings even furniture all depending on inspiration. Something you have created, can be used at anytime if you have the required resources. So although you could craft a massive diamond sabre or golden crossbow you probably won't find those resources early in a story game. Though the games scanning engine helps to find and to dig down to the spot of the resources your looking for. The story and quests are quite simplistic but it has a lovely vibe and has been fun to play, getting to use a glider and fly across the landscape can be quite rewarding.", "appid": "237870", "steamid": "profiles/76561198038114231", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "72", "votes_funny": "6", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1576065600.0}
