{"text": "Alien: Isolation  Survival Horror  Creative Assembly   SEGA\t  6 Out, 2014  81 ( ) What a masterpiece   is. An incredible journey and a spectacular tribute to the original Alien (1979) movie.  I can easily say that this is the scariest game I have ever played and lately I have played a lot of scary horror games like Penumbra, Amnesia and Outlast for example. But this one beats all of those, I never felt so relieved for completing a game, and not because it was getting boring, it was just that scary. This game is set 15 years after Ridley Scott’s original Alien movie, and in it you get to play as Amanda Ripley, daughter of Ellen Ripley. She is an engineer for the mega corporation Weyland-Yutani. She gets embarks on a journey that gets her on the Sevastapol Station when she found out that the flight recorder of her mother’s lost ship, the Nostromo is being held there. Unfortunately when she gets on the mysteriously abandoned space-city, rapidly she notices that something has gone terribly wrong. How awesome Sevastapol is. The   and the attention to detail in this game excels in the videogame industry. Even more when there are so many things so thoroughly recreated to match Ridley Scott’s vision in the first Alien movie. A lot of fan service in this game, a great tribute to the Alien series. The   are also top notch, specially the lightning which is one of the best I have ever seen in a game. The broken doors, lights flickering and steam from broken pipes, all those little details make up for this horrifying atmosphere. Menus are also slick, easy to navigate and straight to the point, as the hud. You also have a good amount of in-game video settings to tweak. The   design is also brilliantly done, amazingly good. It borrows a lot of the familiar sounds from the original movie and has a vital role in the stealth mechanic. I played this with headphones (I advise you to play with them too) and I could hear every little detail vital to my survival with them. You can even track the Alien just by hearing its steps, giving a huge sense of tension and immersion to the game. Soundtrack is also pretty amazing, it gets the vibe of the original Alien movie. In the matter of   its not formidable, but pretty damn good nevertheless. The Alien AI really shines in this game. Its behavior is unpredictable, far from being scripted. Its very impressive and really gives you the feel of being hunted. You really have to get a strategy on how to deceive the alien and be extremely cautious because he can get you when you less expect it.  You also face other enemies like some survivor groups still in the space station, as some androids called \"Working Joes\", which are amazingly bland enemies when in comparison with the Alien. For me one of the only downsides in this game are the encounters with the androids, they get pretty lame and repetitive after a while. The game also has a crafting system that lets you build multiple items from EMP mines, smoke bombs, molotovs and plenty other cool stuff and you also have some nice weapons. The   is pretty good too, I completed it in about 15 hours, I did not played it in a rush, neither went to explore every corner of the game. Unfortunately the last quarter of the game is a little bit weaker than the rest of the game, still good though, but not as good as the remaining of the journey through Sevastapol Station. I also found the difficulty spot on, not too hard, neither too easy, it gave me a good challenge, and made me think about my decisions carefully since the game has manual saves (played on medium). Controls are also good, I played the game with a keyboard + mouse and never had any issues.  The   is the \"Achilles heel\" of this game, unfortunately it is very disappointing. At first you get curious about how the story will develop but soon enough you discover that the story in this game is nothing than just a way of getting you from place to place. The weak characters and bland voice acting also do not help the story. It has some good moments though, but as an whole it is pretty weak.  wise it is almost excellent. I played with a mix of medium and max settings and the game performed flawlessly in my laptop around the 50-60 fps mark.  9.0 If you like the Alien franchise do not think twice, get this amazing game. In case you love stealth games and/or horror games get this one too because you will have a blast playing it. The incredible atmosphere will make you fall in love with this game at first sight. It really deserves to be bought in order to reward the developers for the amazing job and risk they took with this game.", "appid": "214490", "steamid": "profiles/76561198001258474", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "18", "votes_funny": "4", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1433160000.0}
