{"text": "Rise of the tomb raider is one of my favorite game beside Uncharted 4.It was an intense experience from start to finish. It may not be as surprising as the previous installment, but it will surely satisfy your hunger for adventure. Tomb puzzles are fun to solve,combat mechanics have improved  and voice acting is top notch.On top of that dlc adds a ton of replay value with your friends or solo.Rise of the Tomb Raider is a generational leap forward the past one, as the series looks towards the horizon in 2018. A must buy for every fan of the franchise.", "appid": "391220", "steamid": "profiles/76561198251636878", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "17", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1515672000.0}
{"text": "After completing the story of the game I've decided to write a review on the game. Firstly I would like to point out the biggest con of the game, which is the stealth system. The game tries to offer players option to stealth on certain parts of the level but with the stealth system it just doesnt work, the game has provided only 1 weapon with silencer attachment which is a one shot reload which makes stealth almost impossible option to commence the mission. But overall, the game is great with its satisfaction of x-ray skull and nuts replays shots and extremely fun sniping gameplay. It just kinda feels weird that stealth is an approach  in the game as the enemy army gets alerted when you get spotted or im just not playing it right lmao 7/10", "appid": "63380", "steamid": "profiles/76561198060715402", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1544875200.0}
