{"text": "Outdrive is the type of game which you could play for fifty cents in the arcade machines and after you lost, you had to pay again or gome home. That's perfect definition in my opinion. The game itself is pretty slick, the graphics are nice and all, but the fun won't last long. Driving your DeLorean is pain, the driving model is trash and that let's the whole \"fun feeling\" down quite a lot. That's probably the reason why I payed forty cents to get the game, played it once and I'll never play it since. Positives :  - Graphics - Soundtrack - The ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥♥ 80s feeling - Almost any computer can play it Negatives : - Horrible driving model due to which you can't go straight - Bugs. I crashed into a wall, accelerated and I started levitating mid-air until the end. There isn't really much to tell about it, it's great if you're frustrated, bored or in any other similiar kind of mood to ventilate it away, but it becames really boring pretty soon and you probably won't play it if you don't need to. The review is positive, however I would give it \"split-issue\" if it would be possible. 5/10.", "appid": "441870", "steamid": "profiles/76561198113805917", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1544270400.0}
