{"text": "Homefront: The Revolution itself has a great story, but it is so laggy that I have gotten a ton of issues with this game... The game has so many bugs and you might find yourself needing to reset some missoins from the latest checkpoint, also you cannot save, only when the game autosaves for you. You are called Brady and are on a mission to show you're one of the freedom fighters against the police aka. KPA... You have to fight to get freedom and needs to capture the KPA's base so the rebellion can win. You're following James and Dana, who are the main people from the mission and to prove your loyality, you must follow everything they say to gain their respect. You will also slowly gain the people around the cities respect if you capture forts. The game is based upon a rebellion that wants the right things for the city you are in, and you wanna be the best person in the world. I actually bought this game to play TimeSplitters 2, and it takes forever to get to the Easter Egg, but once you have the Easter Egg, then it's all worth it. *Can I recommend this game* Yes I actually can... Weird enough, it is actually fine, but you just gotta handle lag and glitches now and then, if you can ignore that and just follow the story, then you can actually have a solid great game, but I won't recommend buying the game here... Find another place, 30 dollars/euros are not worth it, maybe find it for 5 dollars or something, then it is all worth it! :)", "appid": "223100", "steamid": "profiles/76561198356685963", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1529150400.0}
