{"text": "First and foremost, I have been playing ARPG's since Diablo 1 came out in the 90's. By no means am I an expert in this genre, however I have a good idea of what consists of a \"good\" one. Grim Dawn does have LORE, but nothing too deep that a book could be written about. At its core, Grim Dawn is a loot hunt game that gives you the ability really mix up your stats in many different combinations. There is a total of 9 classes in the game: Soldier, Nightblade, Demolitionist, Ocultist, Arcanist, Shaman, Inquisitor, Necromancer and Oathkeeper. Respectively giving you 81 different duel-class combinations. The game is not as overwhelming as Path of Exile, but really sets its footprint in the ARPG genre with its unique class flexibility. The game is separated by “Acts”, however they seamlessly mend together rather than presenting themselves as such. The crafting system in this game is fantastic and unique. You can create augmentations to your gear, as well as create gear itself by various recipes found throughout the world, or purchased. The graphics are little outdated when comparing them to such games as Wolcen. However, they are not bad by any means. This game will easily suck any ARPG fan right in and they will feel right at home with Grim Dawn. I look forward to the future development the developers will bring.", "appid": "219990", "steamid": "profiles/76561197972224125", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1599912000.0}
