{"text": "This game is well beyond what I was expecting! Of course, being that it's in the Homeworld Universe I knew I would like it, but what I didn't know is that I would like it as much as I do! It's really cool to get up close and personal with some of the ships/art the we all love in the HW verse. I'm still in the early stage of the game, but what I have played leads me to believe this is going to be a fun ride!  Would love to have a third person view as well as we see in the trailer. It's too cool to not have that in game. Shipbreaking...it sounds boring, but the tools and techniques you can employ make it really fun. It's such a cool concept! You really get lost in the job and time flies because of it. The art work is superb, but I do hope we get to see some sharper textures and what not, but even now it's quite the looker! The timer issue does suck, but hopefully they will come up with a remedy that works for their visions and our enjoyment. Highly recommend getting this game! Just get past the 1st few minutes and when you start to get a feel for it, you'll understand. It's just so damn cool! Sure hope we get updates fast and regularly. Can't wait for the full game! Wishlist: Different Music Choices (Homeworld-style) Photo mode 3rd Person... Replays - would be cool to watch the process from different angles like we see in the trailer. :)", "appid": "1161580", "steamid": "profiles/76561197970407447", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1593518400.0}
