{"text": "Call of Duty is one main step in the WW FPS genre from 2003. This game is about the second World War, where the player is fighting in France, Belgium, Soviet Union and Germany, either with an American, British or Soviet soldier. Best thing in the game is the music and sound. Music is really fits for the game and it's memorable. Fits for the action, either you are in hard situation or you are just going through a building, the game find you with it's nice soundtrack. Sounds are okay in the game, sometimes however goes bit silent and you can't change the music sound and SFX separatly, which leads to some weapons will be really loud sound. This is the brightest part of the game still. Let's see the gameplay. You get briefing in thr Singlr Player either from the... briefing room or from your diary or other text based source, and from these the player know, what is happening in the mission, what is the goal and how the war is going. This is really important in the game and I like it. Maps and missions varied, not just with it's looks, but the objectives too. You will explode tanks, cannons, getting documents, hold positions and lot other. For it's time, it wasn't boring at all, but it's still good now days. Fighting against the AI and the guns in the game is okay at first. AI seems to go to cover, throw grenades and every soldier can die easily. Teammates seems to help you in hard situations too and most of the weapons seems balanced out and useful... but if you play on higher difficulties, you will find out, your brother in arms are useless, except few who is important in the game, often let the enemy flank you, not clearing rooms properly, meanwhile the enemy AI is stupid too or have insane reactions on the mentioned higher difficulties. You get different weapons on each maps (most of the time), however you can pick up other ones too from your teammates ir from.the enemy, but I usually played with rifle - machinegun combo (Faction related rifle / sniper rifle + MP40 (or Thompson), because you won't need anything else, either those are useless or you won't find ammo for those guns (on higher difficulties). Pro tip: use grenades most of the times, because AI can't react to it too well. Either die to that and not run away, or it run away, but to your arms. I need to add to the weapons list the tanks, which you can play with for two maps. The controls of those things is not that bad, feels heavy for sure and it's also makes the game interesting. At gameplay, I need to mention the multiplayer, which was one of the best in it's times, but it's still good nowdays, too. Fun gamemodes, action packed gameplay... sadly I couldn't experience this in  it's prime, but sometimes there are servers where there are few players, so I suggest you to check it if you can! I don't have lot of problems with the graphics, except the usual ones (models go into grounds / each other, looks outdated), but for a 2003 game, I don't see the problem with it. I still like how it looks, btw. I mentioned the difficulty, and I wrote about the AI, which is very mixed. There are 4 level of difficulty in the game. I can recommend playing on Medium if you want minimal challange, the easiest one is really about slam the AI to the ground... however Veteran can be hard, if you expect to find medkits and weapons often with ammo... which you can't find it. I played through the gamr on Veteran in 5 and half hours, so the game is not that long at all, which is not that big problem actually, it's good to get used to the multiplayer. Controls works fine in the game, you can configure it properly... but my biggest problem with it, was the mouse sensitivity., maybe because of my high DPI, but on the lowest sensitivity, the game was still too sensitive for me... plus if you change the sensitivity and you play with a MG42 or any mounted weapons, the sensitvity will be the default one, which the game set fot you at the brginning, which was hell. There is not a huge story in the game... except of the history of WWII, but on some missions, there are story lines between characters, but not really worth to talk about those. You can live without it. If I want to be honest, if you want to see how COD started or you want to nostalgia with the game, you can buy it... but to be honest it's really not worth it for the current price. I like the game, I give the credits what it deserves, but seeing this game after 17 years, it really didn't aged well with the graphics, stupid bugs and mistakes in the gameplay, if I trying to be honest with you. Buy the game for the mentioned reasons only and ONLY if it's on like 50% sale, otherwise just try to get COD 2... trust me, you won't miss too much.", "appid": "2620", "steamid": "profiles/76561198082419386", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1605873600.0}
