{"text": "With a game like DayZ it's unfair to pay a meager sum for early access & then complain when something is not yet perfect but the game play is seriously compelling. The reason for the game play being so compelling is very clever. They have developed the game so you invest in your character and care whether you live or die as opposed to other flash in the pan games which are more just quick death matches where living or dying is not really a concern. DayZ makes you work for what you have. No other game has made my heart pound furiously in my chest as when you get into a firefight in DayZ & try to keep what you have fought for. Recent updates have brought some very cool features in. Blending fantastic graphics with chilling environmental sounds lets us know this game is in the right direction. When you have only a few bullets in the middle of the forest & you hear the howl of wolves it will put a chill up your spine. If you have fallen off the DayZ journey I'd suggest getting back on.﻿ This game will become your obsession.", "appid": "221100", "steamid": "profiles/76561198028628766", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1477742400.0}
