{"text": "(TL;DR AT BOTTOM) As I now have 100+ hours I think it's time to write a review. Planet Coaster is an amazing coaster building game that revolves around keeping your guests happy and building amazing scenes and landscapes for your park. You can build a huge jungle for just a simple River Rapid ride or create a haunted house for your little juniors! At the moment, there are three different modes. All three modes are amazingly polished with new scenarios being added for Career often. Personally, my favourite is Sandbox.  This allows you to create a park with unlimited money and a huge area of flat land with a theme, such as an Alpine area or Desert. You can customise terrain, create huge themed landscapes or create the world's largest rollercoaster without having to worry about expenses!  In Career mode you are given different scenarios and a series of tasks to complete. Once you complete 3 tasks, you get a bronze star. Then, you can start on the next 3 tasks to earn silver, and eventually, gold. In order to expand and gain new rides in your park, you have to research rides using your park's money. (Note: I haven't played much of this mode)  In challenge mode you start off like a Sandbox park. You choose a theme and then have limited options and money. You must expand your park and research rollercoasters/rides to build.  Planet Coaster is a must buy game for lovers of the RCT franchise. It incorporates everything from the RCT games and mashes it into one, with improved visuals and gameplay.  My previous cons that had with this game at release (November 2016) have since been updated and tweaked to make our experience much more better. Examples of some the problems I had with the game was the queuing system for guests, the lack of varied coasters and the lack of an ability to place scenery inside flats rides (if you wished to theme them). However, as I mentioned, the dedication the devs show to the community is amazing and therefore they listen to what they want, and as a result my previous issues were fixed. Overall, I think Planet Coaster is an amazing game that implements a lot of features to entertain you for hours upon hours. You can literally let your imagination run wild in this game. Planet Coaster is a really good game with a variety of different modes with hours of endless fun. The devs are constantly updating the game to improve Planet Coaster, and the experience of it's users. Free updates with new rollercoasters and themes keeps the game interesting for everyone. I just love this game.", "appid": "493340", "steamid": "profiles/76561198101249092", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1483272000.0}
