{"text": "This game is a definite improvement over the first game. If you had fun playing Shadowrun Returns then you should really enjoy this one. It has all the same gameplay elements of the first game but makes many improvements that make for an overall better experience. - Improved art style for all levels. - Larger maps to walk around in and more people to interact with. - Better facial portraits for characters - More character backstory on all of your team members. Side missions to go on with your team members to learn their history which gives them more depth and personality. - Skill trees for your crew members. - Many optional side objectives on missions for bonus rewards and dialogue. - Longer campaign than the first game. It's obvious the developers had a larger budget for this game than the first one. If you are a turn based RPG fan there is not much here to dislike. The writing is great. The combat is fun. I gave the first game a score of 7/10 so I feel compelled to give this game a score of 8/10. I'm excited to start Shadowrun: Hong Kong and see what story is next.", "appid": "300550", "steamid": "profiles/76561198074150377", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1543665600.0}
