{"text": "Just recently picked up an HTC Vive and heard about VRChat from a couple friends of mine. Instinctivly I downloaded it right away along with a few other VR games.  My first impressions were of pure shock how fun VR actually was when you had full control of your surroundings being able to manipulate most things around you while combined with dolby digital surround sound, it was almost too real. So far my short time in VRChat has been one of the best online experiences I have ever had the chance to be a part of.  If you have VR, I highly recommend downloading and giving the game a go. You will meet a lot of different people and experience a lot of intesting worlds powered by the ccommunity itself and a great company behind the scenes. So far the community has not turned toxic and most people are very fun to interact with!", "appid": "438100", "steamid": "profiles/76561198070768137", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1514116800.0}
