{"text": "In my opinion, Among Us is a pretty good multiplayer game that can provide a lot of fun if you have friends to play with - it’s similar to Werewolf in some sense, and it is perfect for playing in parties if you have more than a few people who are willing to play it. Online games on their own can be quite fun if people are actually trying to play it properly though, as I have in fact come across some trolls online which leads to the game ending very quickly, making the experience boring. There isn’t much else you can do in the game, and there is no single-player mode to speak of. Overall, I think this game can be fun for a few hours if you have a lot of friends to play with, and are interested in similar types of games.", "appid": "945360", "steamid": "profiles/76561198367090812", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1601121600.0}
