{"text": "A solid survival horror game, with a solid story and good gameplay. What I liked:  - Characters were compelling for the most part, although I wish there were more NPCs to    interact with - Good selection of weapons and upgrades - Stealth is great for the most part - Combat is fun and engaging - Enemies and antagonists were really well designed - Environments were immersive with decent side content to get lost in - Solid story with a good amount of surprising and even heart-felt moments Complaints and nitpicks: - While The Marrow is an interesting part of the game  - Enemy AI and movement could be wonky sometimes. They would sometimes just notice me    behind their backs for no good reason and sometimes they'd turn around suddenly, spotting    me in the process.  - More of a personal nitpick, but I disliked the few parts where it seemed that they were forcing    me to use resources by making stealth harder. Although it could have just been me playing    badly.  - The texture pop in. Jesus H. Christ. Textures popping in or loading slow would ruin    cutscenes for me, since characters were focused and clearly visible, while the environments    looked like they came from a PS1 game.  - It could just be me, but after the 10 hour mark or around chapter 10 or so, the game didn't    scare me that much anymore. I don't know what happened.  Overall though, I would recommend EW2. While it stopped scaring me, there is still a lot of fun to be had. And if you played the first game (which I didn't), you'll probably find even more enjoyment out of it than I did.", "appid": "601430", "steamid": "profiles/76561198102153081", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1573732800.0}
