{"text": "I played the other Dungeons and Dragons game that is free on steam and really didn't care for it. So going into this i kinda had a bad feeling about it. But to my surprise this game is very good. As of this review i'm only level 10, but am finally able to start scratching the surface of what is available. PvP in my opinion is actually really fun. As of now i only have Domination mode unlocked and even though my team was bad i still had fun as i am playing a Cleric and can heal while dealing damage at times. The professions had me worried as most MMO's i have played require you to have materials so you can make things. But in Neverwinter they did something a little different. Instead you use skill kits to gather your materials, which get stored in their own bag space instead of occupying your main bags. You then hire a people and they do all the work for you as long as you have the materials. There is time durations for them so you can setup a worker to do something and keep questing. Overall at this point i give it a 4 out of 5. Been a great WoW replacement. Hopefully the content just gets better as i level.", "appid": "109600", "steamid": "profiles/76561197980178553", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1391515200.0}
