{"text": "Lets get the bad out right off the bat: The gameplay loop in this is monotonous, mediocre and really disappointing. You have probably heard this before but I must say that despite all of this I actually really enjoyed the game. Could it have been better? Yes. Absolutely. The story is great, the atmosphere is great, the protagonist is good and there are some great and memorable story missions in here for sure. It's just that the racket gameplay is monotonous and holds it back. For me though towards the middle of the game once I got silenced pistols I had a lot of fun sneaking my way through the racket zones and trying to clear it without alerting. I understand why people don't like this game but for me I was surprised how much I ended up liking it. Also the DLC's are actually of great quality and should definitely be played.", "appid": "360430", "steamid": "profiles/76561197996990109", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "16", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1580644800.0}
