{"text": "Definitely a great RPG with old fashioned mechanics. (Beware who's looking for a direct alternative to the Divinity series, this is quite a different thing, and can be harder to pick up, especially at the beginning!). Pillars of Eternity 2 is a big improvement over the first title (which I still liked very much). All aspects were greatly refined and polished, especially the base-building mechanic, which is now represented by your own upgradable ship.  There are tons of well detailed secondary quests, and in this game you can approach situations in several different ways too, by stealthing/stealing, butchering everything, talking your way through them, etc. Biggest issue is the loading times, too many, and too long, even on SSD, and this gets especially frustrating when you have to backtrack to deliver a quest, or check if you missed a dialogue option or item (seems like they didn't learn much from the mistakes with their first title). Another negative aspect for me is the gratuitous amount of text (and I love reading). There's just too much unnecessary texts and dialogues options. But all in all, the issues are more than tolerable, and it's still quite a great RPG experience. Big recommendation!", "appid": "560130", "steamid": "profiles/76561198082258384", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "26", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1545739200.0}
