{"text": "Resident Evil 2 Remake brings the highly-acclaimed old classic to the current gen tech. Welcome to Raccoon City in the middle of an zombie outbreak. You can play as two different characters, Leon and Claire, with their own storylines. Your task is to survive. Positive: + Graphics and visuals in general are breathtakingly good! Even though there were some low texture areas, overall the look of this game holds up really well in comparison to other current-gen games. Effects and particles are also really well made. + This isn't particularly a light game performance-wise but I encountered just a few performance issues. Mostly the performance was solid. With high settings the game felt smooth though the fps usually wasn't that high (70-100 fps). + World and level design really suited the horror style of this game. Sometimes you just had to take long routes to get to another area, especially at the police station. Neutral: • The plot in this game would be really interesting but sometimes they took the easier route story-wise. There are great moments in the story but there also are some cutscenes I just wished to end. All around the story is kinda okay but they didn't really take the full potential of the interesting setting. • Combat and movement mechanics are mostly okay but sometimes you just ran into walls or couldn't hit an enemy. Movement lacks the precision and other accurate moves, you only could dodge by moving to the other way. Also the hitboxes didn't really make sense.. Negative: - The quest design wasn't that clear to understand, sometimes I didn't really know where to go or what to do next. Although there were some interesting and well thought puzzles, some required no brain function what so ever and some took too long. Some of the puzzles didn't really make much sense apart from the difficulty. - I didn't really like the idea how the 2 different storylines were implemented in this game. You could choose which character to play first and then complete the second with a bit different quests. I liked the idea of extended story but most of the puzzles, locations and bosses were just the same as in the 1st playthrough. This left the player with some repetitive and unclear plot moments. - Some resources were sometimes a bit hard to obtain in the game and you had to save your items. Overall this game features a solid 10+ h experience of exploring, combat and story. This game might feature some higher nostalgia value for those who played the original but for me it was just another zombie horror game. This game looks great and has some great moments but also features mechanics I don't really see myself enjoying. In conclusion this game is pretty good but I don't think I would pay anything more than 15€ for it, it sure has its audiences. [ 8 / 10 ]", "appid": "883710", "steamid": "profiles/76561198381231125", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "4", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1590148800.0}
