{"text": "In summary, this was a kind of game that you would have in your childhood, which is a good one. Rollercoaster Tycoon 3 was the first edition of the Rollercoaster Tycoon series that featured an actual 3D gameplay, rather than 2D like Rollercoaster Tycoon 1 and 2, which have been quite successful in the past, which still is in newer reboots for modern systems and Mobile, which I would highly recommend on the go.  - The Graphics are dated indeed, however, it still holds the memories. - You can ride all your Rides and Rollercoasters for the first time! - A very rememberable soundtrack, many variety. - Multiple themes to Typical Parks to Spooky ones. - Expansion packs that were legit and not a cash grab, To Zoo's and Waterparks included. - Firework Mixer - The 'James Hunt' cheat to spawn a Jeep to drive and run over people. - Death Wooden and Speed Coasters to demolish guest for fun. - The Park Inspector that you would torture or put in a animal enclosure. - Last but not least, the last successful and rememberable game of the Rollercoaster Tycoon Franchise. Now with the Complete Edition compared to the Platinum Edition, there was a licensing disagreement which caused this to be re-released. Now, I expected this as a remaster, it's not, it's a re-release with 1080p support, which I certainly am happy to use this on my 1080p laptop. However, I do have a issue that no higher resolutions are a option to pick from, why? I hope there's a chance of a update or a configuring to enable 1440p or even 4k, you take the time to add 1080p why stop there? It's still nice though, the game can be bought again. Now for a price point of $20 if you had the Platinum, this is a good buy or pass honestly, it's more directed to 1080p resolutions with little to no changes. Though, if you never had the Platinum, yes, this is a certain buy.", "appid": "1368820", "steamid": "profiles/76561198078811539", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "13", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp