{"text": "Tactical battles with minimal RNG. You won't lose a fight because of a streak of 10 misses. RNG still does exist if you try to shoot a crossbow with a partially obstructed shot or if you have an ability that activated 50% of the time. For instance there's an ability called Strong Against Beasts and when maxed it allows a 50% chance to do a second attack. Speaking of abilities, they come in the form of Mutations. Each class has default Mutations as they level up, and there are what's called achievement mutations which are learned from performing tasks in the game. For instance if the enemy poisons one of your characters enough times, eventually he'll develop an immunity to poison. Or if he waits a turn and then attacks enough times, he'll learn one that causes attacks done after waiting a turn to always be a crit. Then mutations can be extracted from enemies and equipped onto characters in equipment slots. The game really is fun. It's fun to unlock new mutations on my characters, and it's fun not dealing with unfair RNG.", "appid": "1181830", "steamid": "profiles/76561198008929643", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1582372800.0}
