{"text": "Spec Ops: The Line it's great fps shooter set in war Dubai and SPECTACULAR STORY. The gameplay is quite simple, you have few weapons to choose from and couple of granades. You can also command your squad to do some killing for you :D. The game has nice, but sometimes annoying cover system. It isn't open world game and it hasn't offer more than 10 hrs of gameplay, but that 10 hrs is filled with decent gameplay and amazingly written story. Every mission is forcing you to think about it, about consequences of your actions. It's so deep, that you start to blame yourself for what you have done. And the ending...It won't let you sleep for couple of nights. The graphics isn't perfect (It wasn't even at the day of release) but it's quite nice and works perfectly with war Dubai. Interesting title with unforgettable story. It's pitty that It's overlooked. It's also shame, that for less than 5€ you're deciding weather to buy this game or not. STOP READING REVIEWS AND JUST BUY IT !!!", "appid": "50300", "steamid": "profiles/76561198124904411", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "15", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1540814400.0}
