{"text": "Hurtworld is similar to Rust, I am not denying that, but in my opinion Hurtworld is better. Hurtworld has a simplified GUI, a visually appealing low polygon art style, a clean building system, fun gunplay, unique vehicle customization, and you feel more value towards the creations you build. In Hurtworld, raiding is simple yet difficult. There is no destruction of buildings by tools, you must access the building claim, use C4, use a raiding drill, or use game knowledge to your advantage. One annoying thing about Hurtworld is the resource gathering, it could take hours to make a base that can survive against a raid, and even more time getting the supplies to raid someone else. For these reasons I recommend playing on a community server with a high multiplier. I personally play on \"RustyBros\" because they increase the multiplyer for C4 materials. Another thing that I dislike about Hurtworld is the infamy system. It works to lower the amount of PVP, but it also gives infamy when you are defending yourself. Hurtworld does have its fair share of bugs, but it is Early Access. It is, as the name implies, access to an early copy of the game. Some of the major bugs are taking fall damage from small drops, a gun's iron sights becoming off centered, guns becoming stuck on a reloading loop, the ever so infamous \"no touch on server\", and getting stuck on top of storage lockers and workbenches. Hurtworld does not have regular updates. When the game updates it is most likely a bug fix and not content additions. There is a weekly developer blog though, the team at Bankroll Studios share progress on content, new mechanics, new ideas, and fixes to issues here. Hurtworld is in its early stages but it is a very clean, fun game. There are both positives and negatives, but mostly positives. There are several bugs, but nothing game breaking. There are not regular updates, but is is clear the studio is clearly working on the game.", "appid": "393420", "steamid": "profiles/76561198295456510", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1484395200.0}
