{"text": "I'll be honest and admit that this is a surprisingly good nukige. I've played another visual novel made by these developers before,  , and that game wasn't really my cup of tea. I decided to give Norn/Miel another chance, so I got   on a good sale. I had very low expectations at first, but this title is a lot superior to  , not only regarding the story itself but the art style and adult scenes are better. There's also a \"special patch\" you can get to unlock the full game, and it's on the publisher's website.  You play as a young man named Kazuma. After studying in Tokyo for a few years, he decides to return to his hometown. Once he's back, he's greeted by his four childhood friends: Sumire, Aoi, Nazuna, Tsubaki. It doesn't take long until he finds out that they are, in fact, spirits in disguise. Like I said before, this is a nukige which means it's heavily focused on adult content. Don't buy this title if you're expecting a deep plot or well-developed characters because   revolves around certain situations that are favorable to sex. The girls are alright and I even dare to say that for a nukige their personalities are somewhat interesting. This game is mostly kinetic, there are no choices to make, and just near the end that you can make two choices: the first one gives you different CGs and the second one gives you different VA in a certain scene. They don't change the ending of the novel, though.  The art here is good! Sprites and CGs are well drawn, especially the adult CGs. But   which is a bit of a letdown. The BGM is just awful, it sounds like elevator music and I'm glad that there's an option to mute it but not the VA (which is fairly good). The English translation is also better than  . Some phrases still sound awkward sometimes, but it isn't so bad. It also took me around six hours to read the entire novel.  6/10. I recommend getting this game on a sale if you're looking for a nice nukige to play and add to your visual novel collection.", "appid": "748480", "steamid": "profiles/76561198120348301", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "34", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1538740800.0}
