{"text": "> Basic but Satisfying Combat > Unique art-style > Cozy, somewhat dated, yet atmospheric visuals. > Beautiful Soundtrack by Tyler Bates (Composer of the movie 300) > Surprisingly awesome sound-direction. Very lively environmental sound effects. > Good main-story > Great side-stories (Still part of the main story) > Decent voice acting that gets better over time. > Innovative Skill Tree System (Deeds you do can be dedicated to different gods to unlock points for their unique skill-trees.) > Good dialogue system (Like Mass-effect.) > Multiple Crashes and Bugs (Save alot.) > Very appalling intro, would drive alot of people away. > Painful voice acting in the early parts. > Very linear, with only the illusion of open-endedness > Illusion of Choices, but only a few actually affect things. > Enemies are way too spread out, and cannot be grinded for additional points.  > Boss fights are fun, but very easy even in Legend Difficulty.  > Very abrupt ending, conclusive, yet unsatisfying.  > No replayability or New Game Plus. This game has one of the worst introductions ever; it starts with a dodgy badly animated cutscene with crappy voice acting. But believe me, it actually gets better as mid-game, the story just simply becomes alot more interesting and voice actors actually start being pretty decent. The gameplay is a barebone Hack'N'Slash, but it mostly consists of just talking to be people and running here and there to progress. One the game gets right, is its artistic beautiful visuals, the really immersive sound direction and soundtrack. This is a game for patient gamers, and has great story with a very mediocre ending. (Like most stories) So if you're gonna buy it, I suggest getting it on sale. It's got around 27 hours worth of strolling around Greece while partaking in Greek mythological Events revolving around Jason & The Argonaut's quest for the Golden Fleece.", "appid": "12770", "steamid": "profiles/76561198833127726", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1602158400.0}
