{"text": "I may be biased because I love anything Cthulhu and anything Lovecraft but this game surprised me. After reading all the mixed and negative reviews, I was hesitant to play this game but I'm extremely glad I did.  The entire atmosphere of this game screams Lovecraft so I enjoyed it 100%. Audio was very eerie and it just sounds great in general.  Dialogue surprised me with how good it was as well.  Graphics can be great and other times they look a bit strange. This didn't bother me though. I don't mind graphics as much as I do other things like story and gameplay.  I never had any troubles with the game. No crashing. No bugs. So if you're like me and you love mystery, a vintage setting, Lovecraft, and Cthulhu then definitely buy this game.", "appid": "399810", "steamid": "profiles/76561198316928182", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "37", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1583928000.0}
{"text": "Streets of Rage 4 is by far one of the best beat 'em ups I have played in a while. It doesn't deviate from the formula that made the first two such great games, and it does more than enough to breathe new life into the franchise, such as being able to restore your health after using a special move if you don't get hit until you're done replenishing it, and a combo system.  The music's pretty good, but not the best the series has had. The gameplay feels great, Axel and Blaze are back with their iconic movesets as well as some new moves, while the newcomers (Cherry and Floyd) feel like more modern takes on Skate and Max (and I guess Zan in the latter's case) respectively, while still feeling unique enough to differentiate them from said characters. Some people have complained about certain characters having really slow walking speeds, but that seems to have been fixed by patches (personally haven't noticed too much of a difference and thought it was fine already).  The artstyle is fine, I have to admit I didn't like it when I first saw the trailers, but they do fit the game so I can't really complain there. Being able to unlock the characters from previous entries is nice, especially considering how broken some of them are. Overall, Streets of Rage 4 is a worthy successor to the previous games in the series. Is it as good as 2? I wouldn't say so, 4 could have used some more variety when it comes to certain aspects   and a better soundtrack.", "appid": "985890", "steamid": "profiles/76561198043689029", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1605960000.0}
