{"text": "So, I tried the free weekend and... I quite liked it!! ((mainly maybe cause I got 1k+ hours on Arma 3 and I felt at home?) First off let me get this out of the way by saying, after around 13+ hours I have NEVER seen a single \"cheater that killed me from a kilometer away\" or any hacks at all, mainly cause I only joined official servers but idk maybe I got lucky. So, Gameplay is VERY unforgiving if you have no idea what you doing, you will die!! ((but the game is nice enoug to give you the option to kill your self, IF you have something sharp lol just click F11 and....)) but that's ok, as long as you didn't have lotta loot than you lost nothing. I HIGHLY suggest new players to go and play on Empty-low or if you are good at games like this medium populated server's, mainly cause you first need to focus on how in gods name you're going to craft a fireplace,where to drink water((only water wells and ponds are drinkable, I learned that the hard way)) how to craft stuff and etc... took me around...5-6 deaths? till I semi figured out how not to die within less than a day lol. and for gameplay, well...its Bohemia game so expect walking simulator+looting, looting is an extra feature lol you will spend almost 90% of your first few hours looting and trying to find needed material's to live, like finding a knife to open a jar of beans, or cutting tree bark to make a fireplace ((you will need a fireplace or warm clothes or you will die when the weather gets too cold)) If you have NEVER played any kind of Arma games, than you should least have a friend to help you and guide you, if not than, use google and watch some videos. ((make sure the videos you are watching is not from 7 years ago lol)) and make sure to look up the Day Z map on   it will help after you know the game more. How to survive for newbies: this is what i learned so far. I can be wrong about some stuff so, sorry. when you spawn try to find a nice quiet place to get your bearing, then try to find anything, from materials like a can opener to knife, and IF not too risky weapons. ONLY drink from water wells, there located in towns and villages, you'll find it. AVOID drinking any water from any bottle, disinfected first with Water Purification Tablets ((if you find any)) If you find an Axe or a hatchet cut a tree down and make a fireplace, and make sure to put the fire somewhere indoors, unless you wants everyone to see where you are and i suggest turning the fire place when you really need it OH you need either matches OR a long stick and a bark to ignite the fire place plus paper or something like that, oh and DO NOT turn the fire off with water cause you can't turn it back on unless you have a jerrycan/gasoline i would suggest avoiding players that are armed to the teeth...or ANY player, unless there friendly and are willing to help you, or you have enough guns and firepower so if they get any funny ideas the near sights of you will make them get amnesia and forget why they are even there. weapons are kinda useless in my opinion cause shoot one bullet and you'll find your self surrounded by zombies, unless you can hide somewhere to hide. only good to scare off other players or to...eliminate any trespassers on your lawn If you think this is like a \"battle royal\" style of game than, please do me a favor, remove the game and visit your local mental doctor, THIS IS NOT A BATTLE ROYAL!! OH can food is your best friend, if you find any, keep, cause its the safest food source in the game, doesn't other as much as a steak but still, better than nothing, but you will need a knife,can opener or any one hand held melee to open it. That's all i have for now, unless you want me to write for another 1 hour lol but those were the essentials to live for least 1 night. the rest...google it or ask a friend. And as for recommending it or not...not full price, only get it on sale.", "appid": "221100", "steamid": "profiles/76561198052833170", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "48", "votes_funny": "5", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1590408000.0}
