{"text": "Are you looking for an emotional game with an interesting story, incredible soundtracks and decent voice acting while experiencing a game with artistic and sometimes surrealistic visual graphics? Then The Last Show of Mr. Chardish is for you. Not all games about battle royales/PVP, having impossible challenges during platforming/parkour games, etc. Story oriented games could be called a niche genre, mainly created to adults because of their deep thoughts. These games offer much lower playtime than other games while the asking price is still 15-20$+. Considering a purchase is still a valid option if you like to support quality games with a deep meaning instead of buying the 500th reskin of a boring shooter. Interesting gameplay still required to sell a story. Usually, these kinds of games end up as walking simulators with puzzles. The Last Show of Mr. Chardish successfully tried to be different. Each act offers a different gaming experience. You can still find your puzzles, but then you can also expect sword fighting, platforming, a bird simulator and coloring a gray world to bring life and love to it. The acts you experience as Ella, the protagonist of the game, feels like remembering old theatre plays she participated in, but I believe that these acts represent the missed opportunities in life, wrong decisions, heartbreaking missed chances with someone you love while that feeling is mutual. The ending is like a dream, about a world and feelings Mr. Chardish could have been experienced, but decisions can’t be changed… Yes, The Last Show of Mr. Chardish will break your heart. A story oriented game and for those 3 things required to make it sellable and entertaining: A good story, decent voice acting and incredible soundtracks. The Last show of Mr. Chardish successfully mixed these into one game.  Very interesting, sometimes heartbreaking story.  I liked it, my opinion is very subjective but I think it is very good.  Story rich game, it has nothing to offer on the second playthrough, unless you play it again after a few years and you have a bad memory.  Good story, decent voice acting, awesome soundtracks….. Yes, you can forget about the world while playing this game.  Looks nice, sometimes surreal. It is colorful and cute. Not realistic graphics, it provides a more artistic visual experience. . Art games come with decent music. This game is not an exception.  Emotional and not challenging game. The puzzles, the “combat” isn’t hard at all. Perfection time: 4-6h. 1 playthrough enough, but there are many missable achievements and the total amount of collectibles HUGE. A whole playthrough could be done in 3h at first time without guides and chapter select available, so perfection is far from hard. I made a written+screenshoot collectible+achievement guide which include a walkthrough video if you get stuck on any part of the game:", "appid": "1164060", "steamid": "profiles/76561198048659492", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "51", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1604577600.0}
