{"text": "What is \"Shrine of the God-Ape\"? Shrine of the God-Ape is a short action platformer with slight puzzle elements. The game is very short with three stages á five levels, for a total of 12 normal and 3 boss levels. Each boss level has an unique achievement that is not difficult to obtain but in the case of the final boss a bit frustrating. The playtime is around half an hour, with - depending on your skills - 15-20 minutes more for the boss achievements.. The game is controlled entirely with the gamepad. I did not test the keyboard controls. The gamepad controls are nice. One only needs to know that the menu is controlled with the d-pad while the joystick is used for character movement, as well as buttons for jumping and firing. Overall, I enjoyed this game, and the low price is appropriate for the short length. The music and sound are nothing special but fitting. The graphics are nice, and it is satisfying to see the bosses... wait, I won't spoil to you what they do when they are defeated. There also is a speedrun mode, which is not required for achievements, but is a thankful addition for speedrunners. Indie developers who cater to speedrunners without taking away from the core experience of the main playerbase deserve thanks! The controls being fast and fluid as well as the challenge that can be mastered easily and pitfalls to look out for, especially the \"trampoline\" plants needing to be pressed correctly to shoot up make this an excellent speedrunning game. There is one bug I encountered. It can be that the final boss enters an unwinnable state right at the beginning. He is supposed to throw a relic down into the pit where you fight him, but sometimes that relic shoots to the side instead down, and then it won't come down at all. This happened to me the first time I fought him, and I just couldn't figure out what to do... so be aware of this. That said, I can recommend this game to fans of the genre who want a fast game with not too difficult achievements. Recommended: Yes, if you like short action platformers", "appid": "1103930", "steamid": "profiles/76561197979215168", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "11", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1599652800.0}
