{"text": "CS:GO came up with is a great opportunity to play a decent   match. However, if you're in a bad mood and you're not premade with friends, it's not really worth playing. Your team will most likely consist of: -Offensive guys from nameless countries -Somebody who doesn't care about game result -A kid shouting in voicechat You would think, the higher rank, the more 'normal' players are, but unfortunately you'll find those on the whole rank scale. Don't even think about applying your tactics, opinions, the only answer you'll get is: ' ', or they'll straight go their own way. In case they would listen to you and your plan fails, get ready for a lot of swearing and disbelief at your address. If you try to argue with them, you'll possibly get votekicked. This can be for new players who found interest in Counter-Strike really annoying and confusing. Since they have nobody to play with, the solo queue is their only option. They can't really play DM and community servers forever, sooner or later they're going to play some real active match. The only way to find new friends to play with is to add them directly in-game. Well, finding serious teammates is tough. Seriously, CS:GO has thanks to MM such a great potential, but faults like these make talented players switch to Faceit/ESEA matches. Valve should focus more on this and the anticheat instead of useless stuff like sound of a slicing knife. Quality of this game would greatly increase and bring way more new fans. Thanks for reading,", "appid": "730", "steamid": "profiles/76561198048833544", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "4", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1451476800.0}
