{"text": "Islanders is a island building game which instead of gathering materials, you are given different buildings and must place them in specific places to gain as many points as you can to get more buildings and you lose once you don't get enough points to get more buildings and the game becomes more challenging as you move through the islands and increase your score. There are plenty of pros to this game. First of all the simplistic graphics are quite appealing and the game requires the player to think about what they are going to do next so they can get more buildings and progress through the game, Another good thing about the game is it can run on basically a potato which expands the amount of people it is available to. The game is also very easy to play and can be picked up by anyone in no time at all. Also the maps which you can play on are randomly generated making the game a slight bit harder as the odds of getting the same map twice are pretty much zero and this also helps reduce the repetitiveness of the game. I couldn't really find any negatives for this game apart from that after a few hours it does become a bit repetitive as you are using the same 5 building sets until you get a pretty high score. Overall I would recommend this game as the price for it is very good at £4.79 and it is a excellent way to kill time. There is also a world leader board on the game for those of you who are competitive.", "appid": "1046030", "steamid": "profiles/76561198956895280", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1559995200.0}
