{"text": "I rarely recommend games, but I think this is my one favorite in the metro 2033 series. The change about going out of Moscow, the way the story is set-up, and the ending. Oh gosh the ending almost made me cry, that's how good it was. The game has a lot of emotional aspects -> happy, funny, worrysome and sad situations. You grow attached to the characters over the three games, so if something happens to them, it really hits you hard. Extra motivation to be more cautious and work harder! The backgrounds music and in-game music also fits the scenes good, and you can find a lot of additional soundtracks from the radio. You are also able to play the guitar at some point and get some music out of that. I can only say get the game. Graphicwise, for a metro 2033 game, it's a big upgrade from the previous ones, still keeping some graphic aspects from the previous games. Now go buy the game and embark on a journey you won't regret!", "appid": "412020", "steamid": "profiles/76561197998327869", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1550318400.0}
{"text": "Rockstar does it again.  Game looks absolutely amazing on PC, especially at high refresh rates.  I haven't had any technical issues yet, runs very well.  Played through it already on console and will probably take my time getting through it on PC.  Sucks for those that can't enjoy it due to technical issues, hopefully Rockstar will continue to improve the game, soon rather than later.  Online is fun based on what I have played so far.", "appid": "1174180", "steamid": "profiles/76561197986566682", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1577448000.0}
