{"text": "One of the most unbalanced PvP games i have ever played (and i played a lot of them) . 1) Monsters in general are too strong compared to the hunters, if the monster decides to ♥♥♥♥♥ you (at lvl 20+matches) there is no way you can survive, no matter what you try to do, i am not a ''noob'' by far but i do get targeted in most matches because i am a healer character which is kinda normal for monster to do, kill healer= you won the match. I evade, i go up-down the cliffs, i kite around objects, my jetpack fuel gets spent, i kite around the monster while healing my team, when my health gets low i use my self healing ability ( i play as Val), still i die, if i get focused i die, always. 2) Wraith monster........Oh boy, get used to it because that monster type is what EVERYONE play, 99.99% of matches when you are a hunter will end up fighting that monster type. Everyone at lvl 20+ play it because it is the OP monster, the strongest monster in game. 3) How do you know game is unbalanced ? Simply, just look at win streak of monsters vs hunters in every match you play. I tell you this, try to get win streak of 10+ as a hunter, you will NEVER ,EVER do it, while on the other hand, just today i fought a wraith monster with 17 wins streak, after killing me and my Weeaboo team now it has 18 uninterrupted wins. My record as a hunter in 24 hours of playing this game is 7 wins streak. (That happened only once) TLDR :If you want to win and have fun, play as monster, especially wraith monster, as a hunter once you get to lvl 20+ and start facing all the ''pro'' monster players you will start losing.......all the time. @DEVS, either buff up the hunters or nerf the monsters, in particular, wraith class. I had fun in your game untill i got to lvl 19, why do you think your game is lacking in good reviews? BALANCE and the lack of it across the board.", "appid": "273350", "steamid": "profiles/76561198036447939", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "18", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access