{"text": "There's a potential here but if this is the gameplay of the final product than this is not for me. Let's make something straight. I love Turn Based Strategy genre to death. I have 1000+ hours in XCOM EW alone. I also love roguelite as a concept.  What immediately turned me off is the fact that there is no tactical decisions here to be made, and strategic decisions come into play only in very broad sense (does my tank have enough armor, HP left, does my mage have enough mana). Swarms are simply too large to do dispatch without using AOE attacks and all of those cost mana which, as far as I could tell does not regenerate withing battle (and does not fully regenerate after battle as well). This means that you will be doing A LOT of clicking on single enemies while you're slowly being overwhelmed. Even if you can dispatch the swarm efficiently using AOE attacks and mana, the next one will be that much harder to tackle, next one even more so etc.  I think there's a lot to like here. Pixel art is lovely, sound and music are pretty great, attack feedback awesome. I also like the idea of rebuilding the hamlet to support your heroes. I just think this will need to be redesigned from ground up. Either smaller engagements with more tactical options and actual gameplay choices or larger scale swarms where skills are balanced with some system of cooldowns not limited resource like mana.", "appid": "1437010", "steamid": "profiles/76561198083111881", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "7", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1604577600.0}
{"text": "Well gentlemen and ladies after waiting a  long time like fellow fans and have having played the game for a bit now, I can clearly say this is a slap in the face of fans like me and a sad excuse for over 5+ years of development, frankly I feel disenfranchised. But let me say, If your new and interested you will probably enjoy it, you got a blank state and no expectations, but honestly I’d say wait. I got hitched on the hype train watching videos, reminiscing about warband and the memories I had and bought it and it’s clearly not worth it. Especially for $49, it would maybe be worth it at 30.  It’s honestly a aesthetically pleasing upgraded warband with mod features, that’s it. It’s still a grind, it’s still a mess, and it’s empty in all most every regard. There are other reviews that reiterate my views much better, but overall the potential is there and I wish Taleworlds would step up as they’ve grown as a studio and are no longer indie. I get it’s early access but come on man, 49 bucks at this state? What are you, the new paradox interactive? I didn’t pay this much for a half baked traveling simulator.", "appid": "261550", "steamid": "profiles/76561198010863870", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "16", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1586865600.0}
