{"text": "I've been a huge fan of Tomb Raider since 1996, I've played all the games , the last trilogy of the old games were brilliant, but I still love tomb raider II 1997. The goal in the old games was to get \"The Artifact\" at all costs. Lara Croft was intelligent, feminine, confident  and always prepared , she always had weapons and wit and if caught off guard she succeeded in the end and she always worked alone. After Underworld which I loved and the then controversy of the two dlc's there was talk about a reboot. I, like so many fans was on the main forum every day, giving our ideas etc., what most of us ended up with in 2013 was shock! There were several reasons given for the reboot, Lara needed to be more human, she needed to show more emotion, was the main reason. A game called Tomb Raider was released in March of 2013 with a 21 year old protagonist called Lara Croft, an imposter! Even if this was to be the \"origin\" story of Lara, it wasn't Lara, she had no confidence, cried when alone and wanted to be rescued. She \"hated tombs\", so tomb raiding was optional and even doing them there was no intelligence required . Lara blamed herself on everything that happened on Yamatai which was ridiculous since Sam's parents had paid for the expedition in the first place. Lara became the fixer of every situation and in doing so became a one woman army who killed without emotion, well over 1000 men. The story had been written by two woman so I'm guessing there was a feminist angle to all this, the OP female taking on a  masculine world, (Just my feminine thoughts on the story, I abhor feminism )  While TR2013 was a great action shooter it certainly wasn't a Tomb Raider game, but it appealed to the gamers of today that have to kill something or everything to make a game epic. Even though trinity was never mentioned in TR2013 unless you found the 150 gps caches , they became the focus of this trilogy. Rise of the tomb raider , released in November of 2015 brought with it , it's own controversy by making it an exclusive to microsoft , being available on both the Xbox one and Xbox 360 on release day and then on steam in January 2016 , it was an extremely unfair decision for the many PlayStation fans. (as a gamer imo every game should be available across all platforms including Sony exclusives )  ROTTR was more open world , with better but still optional tombs, it had a story that was exciting while still keeping with the action shooter and doubtful  and forever moaning Lara, now even a better killing machine than when on the island. Fetch quests were added to obtain items that had been gained in TR2013 and coin introduced to buy some of these items too. Lara had become a high class hunter as requested by fans of the reboot for upgrading weapon purposes as this Lara has a knack of losing her equipment, but yet she didn't understand ancient languages.  The game was fun but not a tomb raider game. The much anticipated Shadow of the Tomb Raider is now here and is the endgame concerning trinity, it's disappointing as a story. This time it is more tomb orientated but not every tomb is story driven, the tombs are vast and complicated which is the fun part and the areas are huge for exploration, but with that being said while exploring there is no real focus on the story.  Again Lara is acting like teen in a tantrum , taking the dagger is something old Lara wouldn't have done, she would have waited to see who would have and chased them down. Again Lara is blaming herself and bemoaning her lot. Jonah is also in toe which is annoying as it shows yet again lack of confidence.  While trinity is still there the action with them is dumbed down to more stealth , with Lara's new found ability of concealment with mud, turning her into a goofy killer this time. Fetch quests are big in this game and if you want certain items you have to do them as they open up merchants for required items. The skill tree is totally new and somewhat stupid for this game, it reminded me of The Witcher so it doesn't fit in. In one area Lara is stuck in a masked green outfit and it's irritating as is the voice of Camilla Luddington, who speaks without any emotion at all. We also meet the leader of trinity in this game and frankly that is the biggest rubbish of all. This game has a lot of issues too, frame rate drops, freezing , voice echoing , crashing on start up or not starting at all. Lara wont grab on to certain things and some prompts don't show up. You can turn off instinct now, but Lara collects plants and mixes them so she has that ability if you need it, making her a junkie.  While I will finish the game for the exploration and tomb raiding the story in nonexistent and boring and for that reason I'm giving it a thumbs down, but each to their own.", "appid": "750920", "steamid": "profiles/76561198091896139", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "14", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1537012800.0}
