{"text": "If you are expecting this game to be about deceiving people or using deduction skills you should look elsewhere. There are very few ways to deceive people in the game since the infected do not have much to lie about and can kill in plain sight without consequence. The gunplay seems to be the main focus instead using mindgames and yet the guns feels terrible, they have no impact on hit with no damage indication or recoil. The most fun that comes out of this game is the goofs you will have with your friends, however if you don't have 16 players the game is heavily favored for the monster since it's health doesn't scale to the player count which limits the fun that can be had. You will have fun with friends in any game but you can have more fun elsewhere. If you're looking for a real investigation game to play with a group of friends then I highly recommend you try out Deceit, it's also free and criminally underrated.", "appid": "408900", "steamid": "profiles/76561198071891990", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "22", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1599393600.0}
