{"text": "I wasted my money on this so you don't have to. This is another DTG money grab. There are only 2 new routes, and one 'reworked' which is exactly the same as in TSW2020. There are no new scenarios on the reworked route, except for some yard work services which you can find some of them in the previous title.  I haven't bothered to play the Bakerloo line because it doesn't interest me and due to the terrible lightning underground and in the tunnels DTG's games have, I won't even bother. Schnellfahrstrecke Köln-Aachen on the other hand isn't that bad. There are 5 scenarios which including driving from A to B and that's it. Also, they removed the freight trains from this scenario. If you recall, there was a freight train with a DB BR185 loco when they streamed this route for the first time on their youtube channel. The 'isn't that bad' part is the ICE train. I like it and it feels nice going 250km/h.  Preserved collection... why bother bringing all the DLCs back from the previous game when you won't do any improvements on them? The scenarios will be boring again, the bugs will be there again and what's the point in playing them again if you already did in TSW2020? Some pros/cons now: + 2 new routes + highspeed route + louder audio, you can actually hear your train this time + LZB system in Germany + livery editor (I won't bother using it, what's the point) - Sand Patch Grade is exactly the same as before - the scenarios are just getting from A to B (you can do that in service mode) - the clouds are terrible again even though they said they were working to \"improve\" them - pretty much the same graphics as before - preserved collection is pointless if you don't remove some bugs at least - MSB is not available on release date, even though DTG said it will be - no freight trains in Germany - scenario planner is useless. All you can do is set A to B destination and add some AI trains. - countless new bugs. For example, on the first ICE scenario your objectives say 'Go Via...', after you do that it says \"Wait until...\". Why? I'm going 200km/h and there is no way you can stop that fast so you wait for a minute. Please fix that at leas. - only 5% discount for the people that own TSW2020? It's just a re-skin of the same game. It should've been at least 15%.", "appid": "1282590", "steamid": "profiles/76561198060510263", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "145", "votes_funny": "5", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1598011200.0}
