{"text": "The previous game was surprisingly good, right amount of funny and lewd. The puzzles were just on the proper edge of old-timey obtuse but never felt out there. Now the sequel starts strong, but start losing steam just out of the door. The puzzles start becoming increasingly more senseless, Larry gets it on at almost every corner, despite the cornerstone  of the series is him being ♥♥♥♥-blocked in the most comical way, And just to rub it in, the last act is pure filler to pad out the game \"play\" time. Sprinkle it with a handful of bugs, sequences getting stuck, two dialogues playing at the same time, objects missing, all of this leaves a sour taste and makes me feel like the game was rushed to release/pushed out incomplete.  You're better getting the previous one if you haven't, not like the plot of this one will make you care unless you've played the other one.", "appid": "1373430", "steamid": "profiles/76561198003122895", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1603713600.0}
