{"text": "Exowar is your classic top down shooter, it looks and plays like so many well-loved flash games but instead of it being available for free on a website somewhere it is offered on Steam for 7 euros and it's somehow less content filled than the aforementioned flash games. The game has no progression, no upgrades, no choices. The levels are all but one entirely linear, you start with every weapon in the game and there is no reloading or ammo limit in the game meaning the best strategy, and for the most part, the only strategy, is moving backwards in a circle while holding down your fire button. There is literally nothing to it. Yes, the music is nice and the graphics are pretty but the game is so sorely in need for some actually interesting game play that you barely notice it. Some talent was seriously wasted making Exowar unfortunately but the end result is just something that isn't enjoyable to play.", "appid": "358610", "steamid": "profiles/76561197964153663", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1581940800.0}
