{"text": "I really wanted to like this game. After about three years after its release, I decided to buy the GOTY edition and see what all these 10/10's and Overwhelmingly Positive's were about. After 35 hours of gameplay (Pretty much finished everything that could be done except for a few riddler trophies), I honestly don't know why people consider that this is one of the greatest games of all time. First off, the gameplay. It's easy and not engaging at all. It's easy to play, and easy to master. There's absolutely no challenge to it. Even the stealth, it's easy, and the AI isn't very smart. I also found the story uninteresting, and alot of the boss's felt extremely forced, and felt like they had no reason to be there. The dialogue of Batman isn't very good either. The voice actor was fitting, and sounded like how a caped crusader would, but he was given some terrible, cringey lines. The voice acting for the Joker and Harley though, is really good. They truly sound like a psychotic couple, and they're both given great lines. The soundtrack, especially the  , sounds really good and fits the world well, and the rest are well composed but they're not very memorable. The graphics, besides some of the lighting and low resolution on some textures, is pretty good. Now, this sentence is gonna contain some spoilers to the side missions, so unless you're sure you never wanna play it, or have already played it, move away from the blacked out part and don't hover your mouse over it.   Usually if I don't find a game interesting, I'd say \"It's just not for me\", but Batman: Arkham City, isn't a game where I can say that. To me, Batman: Arkham City is a bad game.", "appid": "200260", "steamid": "profiles/76561198099239442", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "6", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1450785600.0}
{"text": "O jogo é bonito, lembrando uma graphic novel européia e é um roguelite/card battler bem interessante, mas algumas coisas tiram o brilho do jogo. Joguei cerca de 6 partidas e em apenas uma delas eu consegui contratar mais mercenários. O jogo já estava difícil, mas piorou. Era muito comum eu gastar turnos e mais turnos aplicando escudo porque não tinha como me curar. Não existem cartas de cura ou pelo menos não achei nenhuma. Quando vinha a opção de cura, tinha um ou até dois outros eventos bons que eu perdia, na mesma tela de seleção. Outro problema foram os combates de Elite que são praticamente impossíveis de serem vencidos e às vezes, era a única opção pra avançar na história. As cartas não têm upgrade. Então, praticamente, você não fica forte. Eu ia positivar, mas com todos esses problemas, acho que ainda não vale a pena por terem jogos mais polidos. Mudarei minha opinião no futuro, espero.", "appid": "1075740", "steamid": "profiles/76561198132136056", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1596196800.0}
