{"text": "Firstly, the game is amazing, no doubt about that. The graphics are extraordinary, the gameplay mechanics are fantastic. It's a great gaming experience. But the content in the game is not at par with the price. At INR 3999, its one of the costlier games in the market, and it has very little to show for it. Lets start with what it lacks. 1. A story. Starting with the Journey I found a newfound interest in sports games thanks to the story mode. In FIFA 21, there is a story mode in the game under VOLTA football- the Debut, but the story is far too short to be that interesting, it keeps us hanging definitely. 2. Lack of official stadiums- The game doesnt include a lot of official stadiums including Camp Nou, probably because PES got their rights. 3. Weird facial glitches during celebrations- I've been playing at 1920*1080 at ultra and sometimes while celebrating the players facial expressions get twisted into weird angles. It's really good, the graphics are fantastic, the mechanics are extraordinary, but still to my personal opinion it's not worth the buck. If you get it on a sale, grab it.", "appid": "1313860", "steamid": "profiles/76561198173422749", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1603368000.0}
