{"text": "I really tried to like this game but I just can’t. I usually like almost every game that game reviewers bashed but this one is impossible to love. The biggest problem is the difficulty. I tried to play with a game pad and it’s almost impossible to get good scores. With a keyboard and mouse it’s easier but, nevertheless, the game is so damn hard. Games are supposed to be fun, to help you escape from stress and reality but with this one, you’ll get mad, frustrated and maybe with a headache!  I appreciate the developer’s work. The graphics are nice and the spider looks cute but if you want to play the game as it’s supposed to be, the difficulty is unbearable.", "appid": "207000", "steamid": "profiles/76561198078448591", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "32", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1412856000.0}
{"text": "This game is very fun to play, very realistic, even their lower fidelity models are great, but there's a few MAJOR gripes I have with it... 1. The menus and settings are the most unintuitive I've maybe ever seen. They had many examples to take from (FSX, XP11, XP10 and P3D) and they still messed up really badly. The best way I can explain the overall GUI experience is 'numb' and surprising (in a bad way). For starters, the controls menu is brutal, certain actions have weird names, certain controls can't be set if you have devices plugged in. For example: you can't adjust the TrackIR or Oculus controls unless you have them plugged in, despite the devices still showing in the controls section, you can't edit the mouse controls while a joystick is plugged in, in fact, you can't use the mouse at all for anything other than views when a joystick is plugged in. The names and application of settings is horrible too, you want to decrease the pitch sensitivity for all planes? YOU LITERALLY HAVE TO GO TO EVERY PLANE AND ADJUST EACH AXIS TUNE........ that takes an hour. There is no 'universal control setting (for things like pitch, roll, yaw, weapon shoot, switch weapon, look left/right/up/down), well, there is, IT JUST DOESN'T WORK... 2. The game does not include any tutorials for most planes... even the ones you buy. I bought FC3, and I love the F15C, but I don't know how to properly use the thing... it's a low fidelity model and the things I want to know (weapons) could be taught in minutes, but they don't. Read the manual you say? I tried, but it's straight up incorrect and does not cover the full scope of the weapons. Also, the manual is hidden somewhere in some folder instead of being accessible in game or easily findable. There are VERY FEW 'default' tutorials that aren't aircraft specific, but these are brutal too, the instructions are sometimes wrong, they're very assuming that you know the names of all the instruments already, they disappear after 15s EVEN WHEN YOU HAVEN'T CLICKED NEXT, so if you're rereading, good luck reading it all again before it disappears. And you can't redo a section of a tutorial, you have to just restart to see that one part... because the game assumes that noobs taking basic tutorials already know all the parts of the plane.... that you're learning to fly... 3. There's no workshop support.......................... in a game that f*cking relies on community add-ons like maps, missions, tutorials and controls. 4. The visual settings are insanely primitive. Does it support triple monitors? Yes! Which 3 and in which order? It's a surprise! I have 3 main monitors and 1 accessory monitor, I obvs want to use the 3 identical monitors to fly... but I can't instead it insists on using Monitor #1, #2 and #3 in that order. The issue is that with a laptop, I CAN'T CHANGE #1 to anything else... unless I shut it off, which causes huge graphical issues.  And again, these graphical issues could be EASILY fixed by following AN EXISTANT settings type, like what XP11 uses, how hard is it to change the monitor order?.... XP does a phenominal job at this, DCS gets a 0/10. It honestly feels like the settings are from a 2001 Playstation game. 5. The game has MASSIVELY CRTICAL bugs, and E.D. has outright ignored them FOR YEARS, despite the fact that they're still churning out new content constantly... Enemy AI are on rails and simply defy all physics on 'excellent' mode, taking away any real life advantages thus reducing the effectiveness of real life training. Friendly AIs are dumb as all hell, they're far too difficult to control and when you can control them, they don't do anything logical... You tell them to engage an enemy, they'll fly STRAIGHT at the enemy instead of formation until contact, then they will go full afterburner until they run out of fuel then they eject... to RTB. **OVERALL:** Incredible warplane simulator with SIGNIFICANT issues that are easily fixable (instead they keep releasing $60 DLCs...). If you have a LOT of time on hand to learn things the hard way and are willing to tinker with controls for hours on end, this game is worth it. But you HAVE to have patients to even consider this game. Don't forget, I bought the simple planes pack... and it's rediculously hard to setup the way I want, I can't imagine how hard it would be to play with the difficult planes.", "appid": "223750", "steamid": "profiles/76561198048974763", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "52", "votes_funny": "5", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1535025600.0}
