{"text": "This game is not very good. It starts out ok despite the terrible floaty jumping and dumb wall grabbing mechanic and you feel like you can still manage.....until you start advancing through the levels and the game exploits the awful controls and becomes exhaustingly frustrating. Everything about the controls is dreadful: sluggish movement, inaccurate jumping, unintuitive wall grabbing, unresponsive button pushes. Even crouching takes longer than it should. When you're trying to walljump you can't immediately jump to the next wall like in every other game. First you have to jump on a wall and wait until you \"stick\" to it, then press the direction of the wall you want to jump to but before you can you have to wait until the game lets you which is indicated by a visual cue from your character -- her eyes will look behind her -- then you're able to walljump. It's tedious and takes way too long. You also can't cancel the wall jump and just drop down. You either have to slide down the entire wall or walljump off.  The game will punish you further by adding slippery mechanics like waterfalls going down platforms or snow on platforms, as if the p!ss poor controls weren't torture enough. Then add enemies that throw projectiles at you from annoying angles where they can hit you but you can't hit them. When you get hit you get knocked back which will most likely make you fall off the platform. The hardest part of the game is not the boss fights. It's getting through the levels.  In a platformer bad controls almost always results in a bad game. This game is proof positive. It could have been decent if the controls were tight and responsive. But they're not and it isn't. Skip this game it is not worth it.", "appid": "291130", "steamid": "profiles/76561198086212592", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "10", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1439467200.0}
