{"text": "This game is a cynical, malevolent creation which debases us, insults the human form, and deadens our spirit. If you played and enjoyed this game, you should reflect on what you've been reduced to -- you should not think of yourself as human.  You may still have dim memories of what it is like to be a living, conscious being, fleeting memories and impressions which you can't quite grasp or focus on.  Don't be fooled into thinking this means you still possess any shred of human dignity or identity.   Reflecting on his view of the trajectory of industrial society, Adam Smith said that increasing division of labor would lead to, 'the almost entire corruption and degeneracy of the great body of the people.'  He believed that as the tasks people were required to perform in their work became more and more specialized and fine grained, people would become more and more like automatons, or cogs in a machine.  The intellectual and creative beings once thought of as human would be destroyed, and we would be creatures which were as stupid and ignorant as our physiology allowed. Having played this game, is there any doubt that Adam Smith's nightmare has become our reality?  Or that our reality has somehow become something worse than even Adam Smith's worst nightmares?  Could Adam Smith have imagined that the mind destroying drudgery and toil which he warned us about would one day become an ENTERTAINMENT product?  One that has been met with critical and user acclaim? We have crossed the threshold into the numbing darkness in such a banal fashion that we don't even realize we are dead.   This is a bad video game.", "appid": "346900", "steamid": "profiles/76561197992051132", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "14", "votes_funny": "10", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1506513600.0}
