{"text": "Oh man, what have they done to my boy. 343i has yet again ruined another Halo, this time on the long awaited Halo on Steam. Honest review, nostalgia behind; lets just hope for some a hotfix of some kind soon. I will indeed change this to recommended once the big stuff gets fixed, because truly this game deserves it. Its a masterpiece as a game but a poorly executed port [Disclosure: Admins, I am basing these off the current game on master chief collection & I also go off the current settings it uses, such as no graphic settings, no subtitles, horrible sound, ip leaks]  Pros -Servers work fine -No mouse input delay- Raw mouse input has been added -Has an experimental uncapped framerate on release, instead of locked at 60 fps, however doesn't really work well.  Understandable though as its in experimental and even a miracle its in the game after they said they wouldn't add an uncapped framerate -Game is fun, bring back good memories -Game is atleast playable -Allows mods -Allows custom games, however getting maps are very hard as no file share is included on launch, also forge not being added which doesn't help -Its Halo Reach on Steam -Includes FOV slider -Incredible classic game Conclusion, surprised the game is actually this good on launch considering the old MCC & Halo on PC expectations, thought the servers were gonna be f^cked However Thrown the 'Ready when it's ready' motto since the start, which lead to: Cons -No forge, No theatre, Fileshare not available, I know they said it wouldn't be available, but its still a disappointment. -Subtitles didn't work, which is just beyond me on how that one got past the flighting when deaf players can't even play -Sound is horrific, sounds muffled and awful -Stutters for me even with 60fps -Lack of graphical options -No splitscreen -Default controls/keybindings are horrible, and yet you can't even change some -Campaign doesn't have dedicated servers -Really bad menu when picking armor and customizing your spartan, Im not sure what I'm clicking on half the time. Old menu was better. -When I tried hosting a gamenight, picking custom games- It's confusing and frustrating -Playing with friends from other countries won't work and is just painful, so good luck with playing with friends from other regions - Along with that, it also cancels the lobby timer after one of the members go 'idle' for too long (Basically not going in the game), after the match tries to load for a whole 10 whole minutes. If you have friends from other regions, I would just keep a prayer, It's pretty awful. -Along with the lobby cancelling for 'idle too long', it doesn't even work properly. If you're customising your character and in game doing settings, it still cancels to lobby queue for idle, when you clearly weren't even idle. This is just frustrating. -Bad progression system, so appalling. -No map voting, in any way, whatsoever. -Easy Anti Cheat kicks users for 'an error' -Ranks replaced with some awful cardboard cutout medals that don't even look good, honestly, how does the Xbox 360 Reach, a game that is 10 years old have better looking rank medals than these awful bland medals? Should've kept them old school, and thats not even me asking for nostalgia, it literally looks like trash compared to the Xbox 360 reach medals. The main reason I grind for ranks is for the art it has and what you can show off, yet it still looks like poopoo. -The new battle pass system replacing the oldschool credit system (However was good in some ways, bad in others): The lack of variety with what helmets & armor you choose because of this new 'battle pass' system is frustrating at best, and everyone gets the same stuff. The old credit system gave you so many choices and was so much better than this seasonal stuff. The one main reason I played reach was to grind for armor, yet they give you this bs, I'm f^cked off that I have to grind for armor for a system that is so sparse and given to everyone at the same time. Before you know it, everyone's gonna have electric helmets. What a bunch of crap. -No dedicated custom games browser -If I want any users to appear on the right hand side like it used to, instead of it collaborating with Steam, I have to add them through this 'Xbox Console Companion' bs.  -Animations have motion blur and bugs out at uncapped framerates, due to the animation being 60fps and your uncapped fps not collaborating with it -Along with this, your WASD animations are locked at 60fps, while looking around is uncapped. It's atrocious and borderline unplayable. -Xbox servers go down currently, quite a lot. -No XP by doing campaign -There is an IP LEAK BY DEFAULT, you can disable this, (by simply going into settings, network, relays, turn it on) however, for the avid gamer first picking up Halo (which is very likely, as people come from console and others who aren't even aware of this!), will have their IP swooped by someone who has bad intentions with it! I'm sad I even have to put a bad review on a game that was my childhood and that's on steam, but I hope you understand.", "appid": "976730", "steamid": "profiles/76561198147274112", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "129", "votes_funny": "18", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1575374400.0}
{"text": "\"good game\", sans majuscule.  C'est comme ça qu'un utilisateur francophone de niveau 536 recommande le jeu. Il se trouve que je parle bien l'anglais, et je peux vous dire ce que \"good game\" veut dire avec exactitude : ça veut dire \"bon jeu\". Et bon jeu, en l'occurrence, veut pas dire que c'est un jeu qui aime faire le bien mais simplement qu'il est satisfaisant. Que CryptoMoneya est satisfaisant. Jusqu'à quel point est-il satisfaisant ? Jusqu'au point d'y claquer plus de douze heures. L'auteur de cette évaluation concise a dépensé douze heures. Le temps d'un The Last of Us. Douze heures. Le temps d'un Uncharted. Douze heures. Le temps d'un Life is Strange. Douze heures. Le temps d'Out 1. Douze heures. Le temps de cuisson des souris d'agneau confites à basse température. Douze heures. La moitié d'une journée dépensée dans ce jeu. Qui est donc à ce point-là satisfaisant. Rendez-vous compte. Ca fait 720 minutes. Mettons par hypothèse que l'évaluateur a pris au total 20 minutes pour vidanger le dragon et se nourrir diversement, reste toujours 700 minutes. 42000 secondes. Vous savez combien ça fait 42000 secondes ? J'vais vous le dire : ça fait 42 x 1000. C'est beaucoup pour repérer des paires de signes dans un jeu de mémoire qui sollicite autant la mémoire que deux fesses posées sur un fauteuil.", "appid": "603360", "steamid": "profiles/76561198095796103", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "8", "votes_funny": "6", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1594123200.0}
