{"text": "Kick-Ass 2. Or Kick-Censored 2 as Steam will insist on calling it anywhere it's mentioned is an extremely mediocre game that tries to piggyback off the success of the two Kick-Ass movies and does so spectacularly poorly. Kick-Ass 2 is at its core a combat game and for this purpose it will send you around to a variety of brain dead enemies that you get to fight using a never-changing move set in some of the most sluggish combat you will ever experience and getting hit while waiting for the game to finish animating your attack is very common and the finishers take an eon to complete. The combat also never changes throughout the game, you get to upgrade your skills or unlock new moves or anything that would make the next combat different from the previous one making every step of the game feel like a drag. The game lacks any extras to the extent that even mid level save games are nonexistent and a death at the end of a level sends you back to the beginning. There is nothing to unlock, nothing to discover. Everything you start with is everything you finish with. The graphics are mediocre which is surprisingly disappointing given the very colorful and unique visual style of the movie and the voice acting, for which they use an entirely different cast than the movies, is especially atrocious. All in all, fans of the movies and comics would be better off pretending this game doesn't exist.", "appid": "304170", "steamid": "profiles/76561197964153663", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1581940800.0}
