{"text": "It's an average turn-based RPG.  Nothing really special, but the gameplay is fun.  There is way too much reading in this game for my tastes.  Endless dialogue with these NPCs who love to tell you about every minute detail of their lives.  If you like lots of exposition and reading you might enjoy this. Big problem with it though.  I'm playing this at 3440x1440 on an ultrawide monitor and the text box is hard-locked on the upper right hand corner of the screen.  Not in the center of the screen like any reasonable game would have done.  This causes me to have to turn my head in order to read the endless novel of text, which actually causes my neck to hurt after a while.  This is totally a first world problem and I wouldn't expect a lot of sympathy, but at least they could have centered the text window ffs. My other issue with the game, and the reason I would not recommend it, is game-breaking bugs.  I encountered one which prevented me from completing a mission.  After researching this I discovered it's a well-known issue that has never been patched.  This caused me to waste hours of time, and the only option to bypass the bug is to replay the entire mission. The gameplay isn't that engaing to make me want to replay an hours long mission. I also encountered a similar bug in Shadowrun: Dragonfall, which I never finished.  I love the Shadowrun setting so I gave them another chance with Hong Kong, and now I've been burned again. This will be the last time I purchase a game from Hare Brained Schemes.  Really a pitty because this game could have been better.", "appid": "346940", "steamid": "profiles/76561197975698109", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1522497600.0}
{"text": "I thought this one was going to be my favorite COG. I prefer a realistic “everyday life” romance story over some magical/paranormal stuff, which is something that most COGs include, so I was not very pleased about the sudden  .  But the real dealbreaker is something else.  This game has A LOT of side characters. Those are nicely written and all romancable. That’s not the problem. I really enjoyed my first playthrough, where every person had some (either chosen or randomized) gender. Problem is, the persons are called by their LAST NAME and it doesn’t change with the next playthrough. So the more often you replay the game, you will get confused as to which gender all of your side characters have this time, and if it would make sense for your main character to romance those or not. The game will ask you who to bring and then show 10 genderneutral / last names in a row.  Yeah, who to pick?  Do you really remember every single gender of those classmates in the beginning of a new playthrough? I also noticed that even the own parents of those characters call their child by their last name. I have no idea why the author thought it was a good idea to choose those names for the side characters. I can only explain it to myself with either lazy writing or a failed attempt to be inclusive. Other COGs change up the first name slightly to signal which gender that person is assigned to during that playthrough. Much more pleasant to read and not as damn confusing.", "appid": "1171820", "steamid": "profiles/76561198155097545", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "6", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1599566400.0}
{"text": "Short Summary: The bad: Horribad game - Cannot change shoulders that you aim from, therefore favors aiming and shooting to the right of cover. Cannot aim over left should unless stuck to a wall. Awful controls - shift/double tap W is either roll or sprint, you cannot bind another key and you cannot disable this option, you cannot have split these options up. No secondary weapon (pistol) - you have a primary weapon (AR, smg, sniper shotty) and a melee weapon. No secondary firearm meaning if you get rushed while using a sniper, you have 2 options, go crazy with an axe and hope you dont get shot in the face or use a grenade to try and take them out along with yourself. Extremly laggy, (although ping is not displayed), but is evident by the fact that you can shoot someone, go back into cover, start reloading and then either you or the enemy drop dead mid reload. Shallow game modes, standard run-of-the-mill lobby shooter with no innovative or defining features. Uses third party account to sign up with - does not display EULA, does not display privacy policy, may sell your email to third party companies. Sign up with a dump email account to be safe. The good: Has an uninstall option. Verdict - You'd be better off stepping on Lego, at least that would be more interesting and less painful.", "appid": "315640", "steamid": "profiles/76561198048323387", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1408536000.0}
