{"text": "I had high hopes for this game. It's a game that had a lot of potential. Said potential was lost due to how the developers started to act after the free to play release. We as a community asked for free to play, because the game's playerbase was so low, that would hardly get a single match in a whole day. The devs actually answered to our feedback and gave us the free to play.  Now, where did they ruined their game? 1st- The developers took away their team deathmatch mode from their servers (the main attraction to the game) and only have 1 game mode and only 1 map. This issue happened before the free to play release, and even after the community gave the developers feedback on how having only bierball available is boring, they didn't care. 2nd- The developers released a \"fake\" free to play game, where you're forced to pay to be able to unlock more characters from the game (you don't have any type of in game currency). You're forced to stay with only 2 characters. In a heavy teambased game like this, being able to have a way to unlock the other characters is necessary to counter other team compositions. Given that freemium users have this big disadvantage over paying users, this game is considered pay2win (paying users will have the character advantage that will help your team and counter the enemy team).  This was also the reason why you see so many negative ratings, because even after all the feedback, the developers don't care. Which leads to the third, and I will explain why. 3rd- The developers are lazy , aren't able to handle constructive criticism and delete your criticism threads. Me, along with other players that actually cared about the game, posted feedback over the months, that is after the free to play release, constantly ignored. Which is also deleted after the developer seeing that is criticizing the game (even if its constructively). I will give you an example, where I posted a thread saying the reason why the developers ruined the game and where they could fix it. The developer minutes after posted saying that I had a grammar mistake on my thread and proceeded to delete my thread after 1 hour  (which is in other words mocking the players that pay them the food that they get on their table, a big middle finger to the people that actually cared about this game and that felt the need to help the game improve). I was once one of the people who defended the game after the free to play release, because I thought that the developers just made a mistake on their free to play model and that they cared about the game. I was wrong, very wrong. Seeing how the developers ruined their game and them not caring about fixing it. Seeing how they obviously can't handle criticism and make their forums like we're in Germany during the times of Hitler (nothing against Germans ofc). TL;DR: AVOID THIS GAME LIKE A PLAGUE! DON'T WASTE YOUR TIME, UNLESS YOU WANT TO GIVE MONEY TO LAZY AND IMMATURE DEVELOPERS!", "appid": "348460", "steamid": "profiles/76561198092081307", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "40", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1459166400.0}
