{"text": "The gameplay in this game is fast paced, and very fun. It runs on low spec PCs smoothly, and almost everything in this game is for free, which helps attract new players and keeps them interested. However, the community is kind of toxic. The multiplayer is dead, and when you finally get paired up, it is always against people with 5% skill and 95%   equipment (attained through several hours of farming or just buying them straight off the market using real life money) that can one hit kill you while you have to land 10-15 (quite a difference). Even after you miraculously kill these ' ' , they just proceed to call you a 'hacker' or a 'tryhard' throughout the entire game, which is pretty annoying at times. Like I said, almost everything is free, but at a cost of tons of hours farming up cash or resources for those items, which most people don't have. Moreover, there are several bugs, and areas where the game freezes and makes it hard to move on in the game's story mode. After searching up for fixes online, it seems console gamers and PC gamers both have similar problems and the devs have yet to fix them. In the end, this game is free, really exciting, and very addicting. But kind of P2W to some extent as more plat can easily get you prime weapons much faster than having to grind for parts.    ¯\\_(ツ)_/¯", "appid": "230410", "steamid": "profiles/76561198151675218", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "77", "votes_funny": "18", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1517832000.0}
