{"text": "Starting off this review I have to point out that I’m a massive Dragon Ball fan, I don’t really take an interest in any of the other Animes, but I have a bias towards anything Dragon Ball. When this game was first shown at E3, I was hyped beyond belief. Showing Namek, Goku and Frieza with the art style taken had blown me away, I was sold on the game before gameplay had even come out. That’s the power of hype though folks and I’ve been proven wrong plenty of times before and I never learn my lesson. I pre-ordered the Deluxe edition of the game at around £75 but I haven’t made a massive game purchase this year so I thought I could splurge my money on this one. I did have some mixed feelings about spending that much, but I thought it would be worth it. The £50 price is the base price. I’ll start with the positive aspects of the game and move on to the negatives later. The game has a massive roster that would definitely please more hardcore Anime/Manga fans, Dragon Ball, Naruto, One Piece, Bleach, the list goes on and on. With the character pass there is an obvious intent to add a lot more characters later on and keep working on this game as time goes on, as long as it doesn’t completely flop. The fighting can be slightly tedious, but I quite liked the movesets and combos. Launching a big bang attack in this game truly did feel badass, along with many of the other signature ultimate moves that come with this game. Now I’m going to dive into the negative side of the review. I refunded this game before I fell into a sunk cost fallacy because I knew that would happen to me eventually. I wanted to love this game from the very start, I wanted to be hyped and watch these different anime characters battling it out with original characters from Akira Toriyama himself. I did not love this game, I didn’t even like it and I regretted it after about an hour of play. The mission system is very similar to Xenoverse but worse, it’s tedious and void of actual content. The actual story is lacklustre and really pointless, the whole story is centred around fighting different anime characters and generic evil beings that can take power and control other people which isn’t exciting at all and no different from completing the side missions or just doing your own fight. The art style is another thing to comment on with this game, when I look at Goku it’s almost like someone spray painted a Goku face onto a WWE custom character. It’s off-putting to say the least, considering the trailer actually looked really good the game doesn’t live up to it. I didn’t have fun with this game either, it just felt like I was going through chores rather than watching the most popular anime characters fight. The final negative point I have to make about this game may be a controversial one, it’s just a personal preference which may be the same for some others too. I did not enjoy any of the voice acting, I prefer watching dub in anime rather than sub and it put me off that there wasn’t a choice. I was well aware before purchasing but I didn’t realise I’d dislike it that much, I’m also well aware that they couldn’t really do anything about this due to the fact that licensing all the different characters in the game is pretty much an impossible task due to multiple rights holders. In conclusion, I should’ve enjoyed this game, I should be defending it due to my bias but unfortunately, I cannot recommend this at all. Maybe I have been a bit harsh and been let down by the standards I gave the game after the trailer, but I genuinely don’t think it’s worth it. I may revisit this when it’s around about £5-10. I’d rate this 3 disappointing E3s out of 12.", "appid": "816020", "steamid": "profiles/76561198073443511", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "66", "votes_funny": "13", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1551787200.0}
{"text": "No me gusta hacer reseñas negativas, simplemente prefiero no hacerlo si algo no me gusta, pero esque no puedo quedarme de brazos cruzados si te venden algo que esta  . No les hablare sobre la mecanica del juego, la cual por cierto sigue el mismo ritmo que su predecesor, sino que les voy a contar sobre lo que me paso durante una misión secundaria y el porque deje el juego. Se trata de la misión de atrapar a un maton llamado Bird el cual se encuentra en un lugar marcado en el mapa como    , resulta que cumplo la misión y antes de salir abro una puerta para conseguir un coleccionable (si, soy de esos que buscan los 300 objetos coleccionables) y resulta que,  , me encuentro en una habitación ♥♥♥♥♥ de la muerte (o Blackroom of Doom si prefieren) lo cual, aunque resulte molesto, no es algo tan raro en los juegos de mundo abierto. Bueno, pues que me dije \"bah, le sigo mañana\" y apague el juego, y al dia siguiente prendo el juego y resulta que sigo en ese mismo cuarto ♥♥♥♥♥ del cual   por ningun medio, he buscado soluciones y ninguna sirve, y hay varias personas a las que les ha sucedido lo mismo, hasta he pensado buscar mods para teletransportarme, y vaya que los he intentado instalar (lo cual ya es mucho decir, ya que normalmente si modificas un juego ya no puedes conseguir los logros, los cuales tanto intente conseguir) pero tampoco me han funcionado... ¿Porque no iniciaste una partida nueva? diran ustedes, el motivo por el que no la inicie es que ya llevaba 15 horas jugadas y la mitad de los muchisimos coleccionables, ademas aunque el juego no sea malo, tampoco es la gran cosa como para rejugarlo varias veces. Reembolsar tampoco puedo debido a que el juego no lo compre por steam sino que lo active por medio de clave. El juego es bueno, si no les molesta que les joda toda la partida a mitad de juego comprenlo, pero si eso les preocupa mejor compren sus predecesores;   y", "appid": "209000", "steamid": "profiles/76561198252336214", "voted_up": false, "votes_up