{"text": "Puede que sea la primera puntuación negativa que doy en Steam, y es que los juegos malos no me mueven a realizar un comentario. Y no, este juego no es malo, todo lo contrario. Por lo poco que he podido jugar, apunta fácilmente a ser el mejor de los cuatro de esta saga. Y es precisamente lo que me ha llevado a escribir aquí, el cabreo por el hecho de que los desarrolladores del port me hayan privado de disfrutarlo. ¿Por qué? Por su pésimo, nefasto, vergonzoso rendimiento. He probado todas las soluciones que he encontrado por internet, y ninguna ha funcionado. Las misiones se pueden jugar sin problemas, pero cualquier atisbo de desplazamiento por la ciudad, ya sea planeando y especialmente en el Batmovil, es un suplicio, un festival de micro parones, de stuttering y de caída de fps. Y bueno, eres Batman, y es un juego de mundo abierto, si desplazarte por la ciudad es tan poco placentero, echa a perder todo el conjunto, por muy bueno que sea. Una pena.", "appid": "208650", "steamid": "profiles/76561198067361840", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "5", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1595678400.0}
{"text": "I've been playing on-and-off since launch, both through Steam and the ARC launcher. * The premium current starships are outrageously expensive. Outside of combo-packs, a top-tier ship costs about US$30. * Trying to buy starships is a test of patience. I bought a US$130 pack, didn't get the ships, and support had no ETA to a fix. After several months, they refunded me. * Trying to buy premium currency (ZEN) is also a test of patience. It took a week for the staff to approve a $100 purchase. * Trying to use paid-for ships is also a test of patience. I was locked out of one of my premium starships, with an error message saying \"Unable to complete transaction: the price of the product has changed. Please verify the new price before purchasing.\" I reported it to support immediately, and it took them 35 days to correct the fault. * Bugs, bugs, bugs and more bugs. I'm talking about characters sitting through chairs, snapping and rubber-banding, wrong bridge crew showing on the bridge, characters with invisible arms and legs, uniforms missing pieces, quests that bug out and become unfinishable, and so on. I wouldn't recommend this game unless you are a huge Star Trek fan and have the patience of Job.", "appid": "9900", "steamid": "profiles/76561197970567205", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "4", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1551960000.0}
