{"text": "I wanted this to be a sort of \"Rock n' Roll Racing\". It isn't, it's just a bad game on so many levels. The controls are sketchy, it's impossible to see what upgrades or advantages the npcs have, there is no skill involved in playing, you just spam upgrades, the music is bleh, there's nothing in the game that recommends it. Everything in the game needs to be improved and fixed for this game to be worth playing. Do not waste your time.", "appid": "284930", "steamid": "profiles/76561198051833438", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1565265600.0}
{"text": "Horrendous net code, you have to disable voice in .ini files to have a decent multiplayer experience. It feels as though nothing besides maybe the graphics have been updated in this version. Mad Moxxi's underdome is still a massive time waster that brings only anger and no joy, General Knoxx's armory still has the glitch to get into the armory, and all the DLC still feel like carbon copies of each other in terms of quests. It's exactly what you'd expect in borderlands 1, I don't really see any reason to play this is you already own the original borderlands. I still had fun, but only because it's still just bl1 and a game i'll haven't played in a long time. Not because the game was 'enhanced'.", "appid": "729040", "steamid": "profiles/76561198066469230", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1555416000.0}
