{"text": "I bought this game based upon the recommendation of a few friends.  My experience was not pleasant. First of all, the game is just simply boring. There's only one game mode with one (fairly large) map. You literally just play the same scenario out over and over and over again.  Second, there is a TON of RNG involved. Whether or not you will find good weapons and gear before being forced towards the center is pretty much pure luck.  Third, the game is full of bugs. Your character routinely struggles to jump over tiny obstacles. These bugs have already been covered by other reviews a thousand times so there's no need to reiterate. I haven't had issues with frame rates as much as straight-up crashes. The game crashes a LOT, regardless of specs. Fourth, it is blatantly obvious that this game is early access. Aiming certain weapons is a chore and often inaccurate, throwing grenade weapons is a complete joke, and there's so much rubberbanding in this game that it's not even fun to play when action is popping off.  In short, it's just a mediocre, limited FPS experience with a (non-unique) twist in that you're eventually forced to fight in a tighter and tighter circle until one person or team is left standing. ARK has a mode just like this, only it's more challenging and implemented better.  Do I think this is worth $30, especially as early access? No way. I got a refund. Maybe the finished product will be worth owning, but for now don't even waste your money because if you want to play FPS, there's many far more interesting options available. I really don't see what all the hype is concerning this game. It's very buggy, unoptimized, lacking in content, etc. Why pay $30 to be a beta tester?", "appid": "578080", "steamid": "profiles/76561198029579963", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1497960000.0}
