{"text": "I loved VVVVVV and Super Hexagon by the same developer, but Dicey Dungeons misses the mark for me. In essence its not a terrible Roguelike, but I feel it is way too much on the RNG side - which makes sense, since you are rolling dice for everything, but it gets frustrating very quick. The artstyle is charming, the music is cool and the mechanics of the different classes are *mostly* interesting, but the RNG kind of ruins it for me.  It also gets very repetitive very quickly, as after unlocking the classes, all there is left are the episodes which impose some restrictions or requirements on you, but are otherwise exactly the same. There are no global unlocks that carry over into your next run or interesting artifacts that change how you play during your run, it is just: choose class, choose episode, go through 6 floors, fight enemies and buy attacks, hope RNG is with you, repeat. For less than $5 I guess it would be a decent game to play whenever youre bored, but the original price is asking way too much, and even on a 50 % sale I feel it isnt too good of a deal. Personally I cant recommend it.", "appid": "861540", "steamid": "profiles/76561198025321433", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "8", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1603368000.0}
