{"text": "I first gave this a positive vote, but that was when i had almost fully completed the main story,liked it and before i experienced the massive grind on all the bonus stuff. I tried to go 100%, but let me give some examples why i decided to re-evaluate this game: 1.The wasteland is big, and full of useless scavenging locations, almost 200. There are mainly small tents with 1-2 pieces of scrap. I drive to one, pick up the scraps, see the \"location 100% looted\" message, get in my car, drive a while to the next tent. Rinse and repeat, over, over and over again. 2. Challenges, 95% of them are completely useless, time consuming grind. And most on them the player can cheat. There are spots where cars spawn without a driver, every \"destroy car with t-boning/ramming/grinding etc\" can be completed there. Every storm challenge can be cheated outside the map borders where there is always storm!  Almost every combat challenge can be done in the smallest of camps. Beat 15 enemies without taking a hit, either endure the combat system where enemies can hurt you before your attack animation is done and negating the challenge progress or find a camp with 3 guys, kill them, drive couple meters away, they've spawned again.  3. This was the final nail in the coffin to me. After all the grind i have done for this game, i decided to fully complete the main story. I got a night mission, i drove to the spot AND THERE'S NO WAY TO ADVANCE THE TIME than to wait. There isn't a sleep button, fast travel don't work, nothing. After all the grind, dozens of useless tents looted and dozens of uninteresting npc conversations read, the game still wants me just to idle until i can start a mission. Have i not wasted enough time already?  I googled it, sat there for a while. baffled, could this even be true? who the ♥♥♥♥ made this decision that it's a good enough feature to put in a game that already is grind-heavy? Then i hit the exit button and thought that this game, other than the story, is a full of bad design decisions and a complete waste of time. I regret buying this.", "appid": "234140", "steamid": "profiles/76561198070591452", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1522324800.0}
