{"text": "TL:DR ----- If you look for a challenge look elsewhere. ----- First of all, it's not a bad game but personally, based on my tastes I cannot recommend it. This game is as you might have noticed, a bullet hell game with maps being generated basing on the background music. If you are no stranger to bullet hell games, as I am, you might find this game really boring. The map is always circular. The visual design is ok, but while using auto-generate mode most of the colour palettes were composed of similar colours that blended together. This is very reminiscent of the \"cage\" type of survival moves in many bullet hell games, its an interesting design decision but it falls short when it comes to execution. The outside of play area has bullet generators that are in constant spinning motion, there are only three types of bullets (as far as I seen) this is fine. The variety of bullet types is not important as long as those are utilised correctly by the game, and that's one of the issues.  It feels like bullet generators just fart bullets at you. In fact you don't really have to dodge the bullets because you have no lives, therefore there is little to no incentive to play. What is the point if you cannot fail? On top of that you get access to infinite slow-mode which reduces the difficulty to zero, as you can play entire maps with slow motion on without any repercussions...", "appid": "247140", "steamid": "profiles/76561198038121294", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1549713600.0}
