{"text": "I have enjoyed Stronghold / Theme hospital / SimCity. And if I comparing 'Prison architect' to my liking: I would rather give this 'mixed' feeling. But had to choose one. TL;DR: Too complicated simulation for me. My enjoyment is around complexity of at most 2 times of what \"Theme hospital\" offers. This game feels like 5x times of complexity of that. Good: - Creative story telling via prison construction. - Fun to watch NPCs working around step by step. (as in Stronghold) - Fine control and zoning (like zoning in SimCity) - Many building posibilities. (Too much that it becomes annoying) Bad: - Process and requirements are too complicate. Complex construction mechanism. Inmates are gonna demand you 10 things at once, like, after basic needs, they will demand alcohol / drug treatments / spritual support. Like while I still busy making them canteen and more housing for new one, the old one now demaning more and start making problem. - Lack of basic building mechanism, you cannot move placed item around like in theme hospital, you need to dismantle it and place it again. (Again, waiting for workers) - Character control when subduing riots is not robust, but still acceptable. Final verdict: - Good if you can handle complex simulation game, else it would overload you.", "appid": "233450", "steamid": "profiles/76561198038807347", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "11", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1482667200.0}
