{"text": "I have now changed my review I gave a few years back, which was very postitive, it's sad to admit this game has gone downhill. Although it has turned very sh*tty I'm staying loyal to the game in the hope that it will sort it's sh*t out and get better, but anways, here's a review Postives: - Ranked competitive matchmaking, meaning you are put up against people similar to your skill level. - Huge variety of maps and gamemodes to play on. - Loads of community servers you can become a part of. - New LFG system allowing you to find nearby players to join. - Very customisable controls, one of my favourite aspects of this game is that you can change so much in it, e.g your viewmodel, type of radar, HUD scale and arrangement, keybinds, crosshair and loads more. - Great servers, always good connection (unless your internet is bad) - Can even run (i must admit barely) on toaster computers Negatives: - Community can be VERY toxic, lots of scammers, sore losers etc - So many cheaters. This is the main downfall of the game currently, Valve has made the game free to play, so if a cheater gets banned, they can just make a new account. - They also make no attempt at separating the cheaters from non-cheaters, by allowing free accounts to be able to upgrade to prime matchmaking status just by getting to a certain level. This allows cheaters to get into prime servers over and over again, for free :/ - Case opening is also very addictive and is essentially gambling - Competitive teammates are almost always foreign, know little to no English, or are just trolling. - Trust factor system is rubbish as it goes against anyone who is just good at the game. I have an extremely low trust factor due to noobs reporting me just because I play better than them. Therefore, I do not recommend this game unless you enjoy being pissed off, cheated out of wins, or can speak multiple different languages.", "appid": "730", "steamid": "profiles/76561198369628655", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0